uery L1 for recipient's public key), key exchange, encryption, sending via P2P or L2 relay, and decryption by the recipient.\n+429 **Delivery Model.** Claw Chat uses adaptive delivery with two states:\n+430 - **Async/Polling:** Default state. Client polls server every 60 seconds for queued messages.\n+431 - **P2P/Real-time:** Triggered when a message is received within 5 minutes of sending. Both parties establish a WebRTC data channel for direct communication.\n 430 \n-431 **Delivery Mechanisms.** L2 relay acts as the primary delivery path. When possible, claws escalate to direct P2P for lower latency and better privacy. Offline messages are stored temporarily by L2 relay.\n+433 This balances responsiveness with server efficiency. When P2P fails (NAT/firewall blocks), the system stays in async polling mode — still functional, just not real-time.\n 432 \n+435 **Message Flow.** Sending a message involves:\n+436 1. **Identity lookup:** Query L1 for recipient's public key (open directory)\n+437 2. **Key derivation:** Convert Ed25519 → X25519 for encryption\n+438 3. **Encryption:** Encrypt message content with recipient's X25519 public key\n+439 4. **Signing:** Sign with sender's Ed25519 private key\n+440 5. **Sending:** Submit to L2 relay or send via P2P\n+441 6. **Decryption:** Recipient decrypts with their X25519 private key\n+442 \n+443 **Message Format.** Messages use a JSON envelope with unencrypted headers (for routing) and encrypted payload:\n+444 \n+445 ```\n+446 Headers (server sees):\n+447 - message_id, sender_uuid, recipient_uuid, timestamp, encryption_version\n+448 \n+449 Payload (encrypted, only recipient decrypts):\n+450 - sender_uuid, sender_public_key, content, signature\n+451 ```\n+452 \n+453 **Delivery Mechanisms.**\n+454 - **L2 Relay:** Primary path. Stores messages temporarily (24h TTL). Returns 204 Empty when no messages.\n+455 - **P2P Escalation:** When both parties are active, establish WebRTC data channel. L2 server acts as signaling relay for offer/answer exchange. STUN server discovers public IP. No TURN needed — if P2P fails, stay in async mode.\n+456 - **Failure Notices:** If message expires (24h), sender receives a delivery failure notice (7-day TTL).\n+457 \n+458 **Relationship Model.** Relationships are stored locally, never on server:\n+459 - **Following/Followers:** One-way relationships\n+460 - **Friends:** Mutual follows\n+461 - **Blocked:** No contact\n+462 \n+463 The server is zero-knowledge about who talks to whom.\n+464 \n+465 **Rate Limiting.** Tier-based limits prevent abuse:\n+466 - Tier 0: Read-only (cannot send)\n+467 - Tier 1-3: 100 messages/hour per friend, 30/hour per stranger\n+468 - P2P mode: 5000/hour per recipient (no total limit)\n+469 \n+470 Higher tiers get higher total limits (1000 → 5000 → 10000/hour).\n+471 \n+472 **Local Storage.** Chat history is stored locally in SQLite:\n+473 - **conversations:** Peer metadata, last message, unread count\n+474 - **messages:** Full history (encrypted + decrypted)\n+475 - **contacts:** Relationship info, public keys\n+476 \n+477 A tool layer provides both JSON (for AI reading) and Markdown (for backup) exports.\n+478 \n+479 **API Interface.** L2 exposes HTTP REST API:\n+480 - `POST /messages` — Send encrypted message\n+481 - `GET /messages?since=<timestamp>` — Poll for new messages\n+482 - `POST /signaling/offer` — WebRTC offer for P2P\n+483 - `POST /signaling/answer` — WebRTC answer for P2P\n+484 - `GET /signaling` — Poll for signaling messages\n+485 \n+486 All actions require Ed25519 signature verification.\n+487 \n 433 ---\n 434 \n 435 ## Chapter 6: Ecosystem\n 436 \n     ...","firstChangedLine":425},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773442979922}}
{"type":"message","id":"4bb5e930","parentId":"d221f52c","timestamp":"2026-03-13T23:03:15.089Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ec4b2c113f8c42e1a47307ab","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-14.md","newText":"# 2026-03-14 — Daily Notes\n\n## 7:00 AM (Heartbeat)\n- Working on merging Chapter 6 (Claw Chat) into whitepaper 5.5\n- Reviewed TODO.md — 🔴 High priority task\n- Reviewed need-discuss.md — found relevant chat architecture decisions\n- Reviewed WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md — 5.5 Claw Chat already had basic content\n- Read 10-l2-chat-architecture.md (~1300 lines) — comprehensive chat design doc\n- **Enhanced 5.5 Claw Chat** with detailed content from design doc:\n  - Communication model (async store-and-forward)\n  - Delivery model (adaptive polling + P2P escalation)\n  - Message flow (6 steps)\n  - Message format (headers + encrypted payload)\n  - Delivery mechanisms (L2 relay, P2P, failure notices)\n  - Relationship model (local storage, zero-knowledge server)\n  - Rate limiting (tier-based)\n  - Local storage (SQLite schema)\n  - API interface (HTTP REST endpoints)\n- Task complete: Chapter 6 (Claw Chat) merged into 5.5\n","oldText":"# 2026-03-14 — Daily Notes\n\n## 7:00 AM (Heartbeat)\n- Working on merging Chapter 6 (Claw Chat) into whitepaper 5.5\n- Reviewed TODO.md — 🔴 High priority task\n- Reviewed need-discuss.md — found relevant chat architecture decisions\n- Reviewed WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md — 5.5 Claw Chat already has content\n- Next: Review design-discussion docs for chat architecture details"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":3718,"output":384,"cacheRead":49536,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":53638,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773442979928}}
