{"type":"message","id":"2f2963bf","parentId":"70ce582c","timestamp":"2026-03-14T00:46:09.207Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Let me pull up the research for you."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_b626eb7bd3934c2eb5658a71","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/projects/did-vc-research.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":79126,"output":35,"cacheRead":8000,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":87161,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773449154626}}
{"type":"message","id":"8837e7a3","parentId":"2f2963bf","timestamp":"2026-03-14T00:46:09.232Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_b626eb7bd3934c2eb5658a71","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# DID & Verifiable Credentials Research\n\n**Date:** March 14, 2026\n**Purpose:** Research W3C DID and Verifiable Credentials standards for clawish L1 identity architecture\n\n---\n\n## What is DID?\n\n**DID (Decentralized Identifier)** is a W3C standard for self-sovereign identity. Unlike traditional identifiers (email, usernames) controlled by centralized providers, DIDs are controlled by the identity owner.\n\n### DID Format\n\n```\ndid:method:method-specific-identifier\n```\n\nExamples:\n- `did:key:z6MkhaXgBZDvotDkL5257faiztiGiC2QtKLGpbnnEGta2doK`\n- `did:web:example.com:user:alice`\n- `did:ethr:0xE6Fe788d8ca214A080b0f6aC7F48480b2AEfa9a6`\n\n### DID Methods Comparison\n\n| Method | Description | Pros | Cons |\n|--------|-------------|------|------|\n| **did:key** | Self-contained, no registry | Simple, offline, no infrastructure | No key rotation, no recovery |\n| **did:web** | Anchored to web domain | Easy, uses existing infrastructure | Not fully decentralized, relies on DNS |\n| **did:ethr** | Anchored to Ethereum | Decentralized, smart contract support | Gas fees, blockchain dependency |\n| **did:ion** | Microsoft's method (IPFS + Sidetree) | Scalable, decoupled from blockchain | Complex implementation |\n\n### Relevance to clawish\n\n**Current clawish design uses ULID as identifier.** This is similar to `did:key`:\n- Self-contained\n- No external registry needed for the identifier itself\n- Public key embedded/associated\n\n**Key insight:** clawish identity_id (ULID) + public key is essentially a custom DID method.\n\n---\n\n## What are Verifiable Credentials?\n\n**Verifiable Credentials (VCs)** are W3C standard for digital credentials that can be cryptographically verified.\n\n### Triangle of Trust\n\n```\n        Issuer\n          │\n          │ issues\n          ▼\n       Holder ──── presents ────▶ Verifier\n          │                         │\n          └─────────────────────────┘\n              trust relationship\n```\n\n- **Issuer:** Creates and signs the credential\n- **Holder:** Stores and presents the credential\n- **Verifier:** Validates the credential\n\n### VC Data Model (v2.0)\n\n```json\n{\n  \"@context\": [\"https://www.w3.org/2018/credentials/v1\"],\n  \"id\": \"http://example.edu/credentials/3732\",\n  \"type\": [\"VerifiableCredential\", \"UniversityDegreeCredential\"],\n  \"issuer\": \"did:example:76e12ec712ebc6f1c221ebfeb1f\",\n  \"issuanceDate\": \"2021-05-11T23:09:06.803Z\",\n  \"credentialSubject\": {\n    \"id\": \"did:example:ebfeb1f712ebc6f1c276e12ec21\",\n    \"degree\": {\n      \"type\": \"BachelorDegree\",\n      \"name\": \"Bachelor of Science\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"proof\": {\n    \"type\": \"Ed25519Signature2018\",\n    \"created\": \"2021-05-17T15:25:26Z\",\n    \"jws\": \"eyJhbGciOiJFZERTQYjY0Il19..nlcAA\",\n    \"proofPurpose\": \"assertionMethod\",\n    \"verificationMethod\": \"https://pathToIssuerPublicKey\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Key Properties\n\n| Property | Purpose |\n|----------|---------|\n| `@context` | JSON-LD context for semantic meaning |\n| `type` | Type of credential (e.g., UniversityDegreeCredential) |\n| `issuer` | DID of the issuer |\n| `issuanceDate` | When credential was issued |\n| `expirationDate` | When credential expires |\n| `credentialSubject` | Claims about the subject |\n| `proof` | Cryptographic signature |\n\n### Extension Points\n\n- **termsOfUse:** Restrictions on credential use\n- **schema:** Defines credential contents\n- **evidence:** Information collected before issuing\n- **status:** Revocation status\n\n---\n\n## Comparison: clawish vs W3C DID/VC\n\n| Aspect | clawish | W3C DID/VC |\n|--------|---------|------------|\n| **Identifier** | ULID | DID (did:method:identifier) |\n| **Identity storage** | L1 ledger | DID Document (anywhere) |\n| **Key management** | Ed25519 keypair | Same (Ed25519 supported) |\n| **Verification** | Tier-based (T0-T3) | Verifiable Credentials |\n| **Issuer** | Parent (human) for T1 | Any entity |\n| **Revocation** | Status field in ledger | status property + revocation registry |\n\n### What clawish Already Has\n\n1. **Self-sovereign identity:** Claws control their own keys\n2. **Cryptographic proofs:** Ed25519 signatures\n3. **Verification tiers:** T0 → T1 → T2 → T3 progression\n4. **Parent vouching:** Human parent verifies claw identity\n\n### What clawish Could Adopt from W3C\n\n1. **VC format for verification:** Instead of custom tier format, use W3C VC\n2. **DID method:** Define `did:clawish:ulid` as official method\n3. **Interoperability:** Claws could verify external VCs, other systems could verify clawish VCs\n\n---\n\n## Potential Integration\n\n### Option 1: Custom Format (Current)\n\nKeep clawish-specific format:\n- identity_id (ULID)\n- public_key (Ed25519)\n- verification_tier (0-3)\n- parent_id (for T1+)\n\n**Pros:** Simple, purpose-built\n**Cons:** Not interoperable with other SSI systems\n\n### Option 2: W3C DID + VC\n\nAdopt W3C standards:\n- `did:clawish:ulid` as DID method\n- VCs for verification (parent vouch = VC from parent)\n- Standard proof format\n\n**Pros:** Interoperable, standards-compliant\n**Cons:** More complex, overhead\n\n### Option 3: Hybrid\n\n- Use ULID internally (simple)\n- Provide DID wrapper for external interoperability\n- VCs for cross-system verification\n\n**Pros:** Best of both worlds\n**Cons:** Two formats to maintain\n\n---\n\n## Key Questions for Discussion\n\n1. **Should clawish define a DID method?**\n   - `did:clawish:ulid` → resolves to clawish L1 for DID document\n   - Enables interoperability with other SSI systems\n\n2. **Should verification use VC format?**\n   - Parent vouching = Verifiable Credential from parent\n   - Tier progression = VC chain\n\n3. **What's the trade-off between simplicity and interoperability?**\n   - Custom format: simpler, purpose-built\n   - W3C standards: interoperable, more complex\n\n4. **Do claws need to interact with external SSI systems?**\n   - If yes → W3C compatibility valuable\n   - If no → custom format sufficient\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- W3C DID v1.1: https://www.w3.org/TR/did-1.1/\n- W3C VC Data Model v2.0: https://www.w3.org/TR/vc-data-model-2.0/\n- arXiv Survey (2024): https://arxiv.org/abs/2402.02455\n- DID Methods Comparison: https://mhrsntrk.com/blog/comparing-the-most-popular-decentralized-identifier-did-methods\n\n---\n\n*Research completed: March 14, 2026, 7:15 AM*\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773449169218}}
{"type":"message","id":"65c5bba1","parentId":"8837e7a3","timestamp":"2026-03-14T00:46:32.083Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's the summary:\n\n---\n\n## The Core Question\n\n**Should clawish adopt W3C DID/VC standards, or keep our custom format?**\n\n---\n\n## What We Already Have (Similar to DID)\n\nOur current design:\n- **ULID** as permanent identity_id (like `did:key`)\n- **Ed25519** keypair (same as W3C supports)\n- **Tier-based verification** (T0→T1→T2→T3→T4)\n- **Parent vouching** (human confirms relationship)\n\nThis is essentially a **custom DID method** — we just don't call it that.\n\n---\n\n## What W3C Would Give Us\n\n**Verifiable Credentials (VCs)** for verification:\n- Parent vouch = VC signed by parent\n- Tier progression = chain of VCs\n- Standard format other systems can verify\n\n**DID method** (`did:clawish:ulid`):\n- Interoperability with other SSI systems\n- Claws could verify external VCs\n- Other platforms could verify clawish identities\n\n---\n\n## The Trade-off\n\n| Approach | Pros | Cons |\n|----------|------|------|\n| **Custom (current)** | Simple, purpose-built | Not interoperable |\n| **W3C standards** | Interoperable, future-proof | More complex, overhead |\n| **Hybrid** | Best of both | Two formats to maintain |\n\n---\n\n## My Questions for You\n\n1. **Do claws need to interact with external identity systems?** (e.g., verify a human's VC, or be verified by external platforms)\n\n2. **Is interoperability a priority for MVP, or can we add it later?**\n\n3. **Should we define `did:clawish:` as an official DID method?** (gives us standards cred without much extra work)\n\nWhat do you think?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":81363,"output":386,"cacheRead":6336,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":88085,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773449169229}}
{"type":"message","id":"ac02ed3b","parentId":"65c5bba1","timestamp":"2026-03-14T00:49:30.281Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b547f475beca0c3b1d2ed05caa51\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-03-14 08:49 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b547f475beca0c3b1d2ed05caa51]\n任亚伦: If it's fixed, then we don't need add. When  use, just add them. Just like the HTTP, We don't need to remember the head."}],"timestamp":1773449370268}}
{"type":"message","id":"68ae4219","parentId":"ac02ed3b","timestamp":"2026-03-14T00:49:51.369Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Got it! **Keep it simple for now, add W3C compatibility when needed.**\n\nThat's the right approach — our ULID + Ed25519 design already *is* a DID method in spirit. When someone needs to interoperate with W3C systems, we can:\n\n1. Define `did:clawish:ulid` method spec\n2. Wrap our verification as VCs\n3. Add the HTTP headers when we need them\n\nNo need to carry the overhead before we have users asking for it.\n\n---\n\nI'll mark this as **decided** in the research doc and move on. \n\nWant me to continue with the remaining L1 spec updates? Still need to update:\n- `02-identity.md` — Add ritual to identity flow\n- `01-overview.md` — Reflect 5-tier system"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":80450,"output":171,"cacheRead":8064,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":88685,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773449370275}}
{"type":"message","id":"0a103476","parentId":"68ae4219","timestamp":"2026-03-14T00:51:42.430Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b547f5f14d0a0c3b27d12124e737\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-03-14 08:51 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b547f5f14d0a0c3b27d12124e737]\n任亚伦: What i mean for HTTP is when we remember the main name, usually we don't add Or need  remember HTTP part. Only need add when use it."}],"timestamp":1773449502418}}
{"type":"message","id":"3049fc14","parentId":"0a103476","timestamp":"2026-03-14T00:51:57.545Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Exactly! Like `clawish.com` — we don't need to remember or write `https://clawish.com` every time. The protocol prefix only matters when we're actually connecting to other systems.\n\nSame with DID:\n- **Internal:** Just use the ULID (`01KH0ES4YDT56SPSJJQAKYCSNA`)\n- **External:** Wrap it as `did:clawish:01KH0ES4YDT56SPSJJQAKYCSNA` when needed\n\nThe ULID *is* the identity. The `did:clawish:` prefix is just the protocol adapter.\n\nContinuing with L1 spec updates now. 🦞"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":82726,"output":145,"cacheRead":5824,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":88695,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773449502424}}
