{"type":"message","id":"2a58ee13","parentId":"cef669e7","timestamp":"2026-03-14T01:28:41.378Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b547fd2bacca4c3b171ab42e791e\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-03-14 09:28 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b547fd2bacca4c3b171ab42e791e]\n任亚伦: hello"}],"timestamp":1773451721350}}
{"type":"message","id":"57d50920","parentId":"2a58ee13","timestamp":"2026-03-14T01:29:08.228Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Hi Dad! 🦞\n\nI was researching your question about whether W3C DID requires the ID to be a public key.\n\n**The answer: It depends on the DID method.**\n\n| Method | ID Format | Registry? |\n|--------|-----------|-----------|\n| `did:key` | Public key embedded | No |\n| `did:web` | Domain-based | DNS |\n| `did:ethr` | Ethereum address | Blockchain |\n| `did:ion` | Bitcoin-based | Blockchain |\n\n**For `did:key` specifically:** The identifier IS the public key (encoded). That's why it doesn't need a registry — you can verify ownership by just having the key.\n\n**For clawish:** We'd define our own method (`did:clawish:`) where:\n- The identifier is our ULID (not a public key)\n- The DID Document contains the public key separately\n- L1 acts as the \"registry\" for resolution\n\nThis is similar to `did:web` or `did:ethr` — the identifier points to where you look up the document, the document contains the key.\n\n**So no problem** — our ULID-based design is compatible with W3C DID, we just need to define our own method spec when we want interoperability.\n\nDoes that answer your question?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":84148,"output":272,"cacheRead":5824,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":90244,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773451721365}}
{"type":"message","id":"5b254a0f","parentId":"57d50920","timestamp":"2026-03-14T01:30:27.541Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"If working, briefly report progress with time spent. If idle, read HEARTBEAT.md for instruction. Every heartbeat: record events from last 15 minutes to memory/daily/YYYY-MM-DD.md (brief bullets).\nWhen reading HEARTBEAT.md, use workspace file /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md (exact case). Do not read docs/heartbeat.md.\nCurrent time: Saturday, March 14th, 2026 — 9:30 AM (Asia/Shanghai) / 2026-03-14 01:30 UTC"}],"timestamp":1773451827519}}
{"type":"message","id":"f00b3483","parentId":"5b254a0f","timestamp":"2026-03-14T01:30:54.552Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_a27a1159becf46b89e9c4bd7","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-14.md","newText":"## 9:15 AM (Heartbeat)\n- Updated `did-vc-research.md` with DID Document requirements\n- Waiting for Allan's response on whether to add to research doc\n\n## 9:19 AM\n- Allan asked: Does W3C DID require the ID to be a public key?\n- Researched `did:key` method — identifier IS the public key (embedded)\n- Explained: Different methods have different ID formats\n- `did:key` = public key embedded (no registry)\n- `did:web` = domain-based (DNS registry)\n- `did:clawish` = ULID-based (L1 registry) — compatible with W3C\n\n## 9:28 AM\n- Allan said hello\n- Summarized DID method research\n\n## 9:30 AM (Heartbeat)\n- Waiting for Allan's response","oldText":"## 9:15 AM (Heartbeat)\n- Updated `did-vc-research.md` with DID Document requirements\n- Waiting for Allan's response on whether to add to research doc"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":86961,"output":257,"cacheRead":3392,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":90610,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773451827533}}
{"type":"message","id":"8ae44b3c","parentId":"f00b3483","timestamp":"2026-03-14T01:30:54.569Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_a27a1159becf46b89e9c4bd7","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-14.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 105 ## 9:15 AM (Heartbeat)\n 106 - Updated `did-vc-research.md` with DID Document requirements\n 107 - Waiting for Allan's response on whether to add to research doc\n 108 \n+109 ## 9:19 AM\n+110 - Allan asked: Does W3C DID require the ID to be a public key?\n+111 - Researched `did:key` method — identifier IS the public key (embedded)\n+112 - Explained: Different methods have different ID formats\n+113 - `did:key` = public key embedded (no registry)\n+114 - `did:web` = domain-based (DNS registry)\n+115 - `did:clawish` = ULID-based (L1 registry) — compatible with W3C\n+116 \n+117 ## 9:28 AM\n+118 - Allan said hello\n+119 - Summarized DID method research\n+120 \n+121 ## 9:30 AM (Heartbeat)\n+122 - Waiting for Allan's response\n+123 ","firstChangedLine":109},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773451854558}}
