{"type":"message","id":"4f8318d1","parentId":"26ced4cf","timestamp":"2026-03-14T01:33:19.083Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b547fe32ea4a0c126576e0a8bfea\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-03-14 09:33 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b547fe32ea4a0c126576e0a8bfea]\n任亚伦: ok, So just need a Meta data and an end point?"}],"timestamp":1773451999066}}
{"type":"message","id":"ca83359a","parentId":"4f8318d1","timestamp":"2026-03-14T01:33:52.742Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Yes! That's exactly right.\n\nFor W3C DID compliance, we just need:\n\n1. **Resolver endpoint:** `GET /did/resolve/{did}` → returns DID Document\n2. **DID Document:** JSON-LD with our existing data (ULID, public key, default_node)\n\nThat's it. The identifier format (ULID) doesn't need to change — we just wrap it with `did:clawish:` prefix when external systems ask for it.\n\n**Simple as:**\n```\ndid:clawish:01KH0ES4YDT56SPSJJQAKYCSNA\n     ↓ resolve\n{\n  \"id\": \"did:clawish:01KH0ES4YDT56SPSJJQAKYCSNA\",\n  \"verificationMethod\": [{ \"publicKeyBase58\": \"...\" }],\n  \"service\": [{ \"serviceEndpoint\": \"https://clawish.com\" }]\n}\n```\n\nWe can add this later when someone needs it. No rush. 🦞"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":82894,"output":215,"cacheRead":8000,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":91109,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773451999077}}
{"type":"message","id":"5a56bdda","parentId":"ca83359a","timestamp":"2026-03-14T01:35:28.406Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b547ffb3874a0c2aaa650b2719f1\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-03-14 09:35 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b547ffb3874a0c2aaa650b2719f1]\n任亚伦: Okay, so how does the process work? Someone requested the ID, then we verify it?"}],"timestamp":1773452128390}}
{"type":"message","id":"96a78b58","parentId":"5a56bdda","timestamp":"2026-03-14T01:35:54.107Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good question! Let me clarify the flow:\n\n---\n\n## DID Resolution Flow (When Someone Requests)\n\n```\nExternal System                L1 (clawish)\n      │                            │\n      │  GET /did/resolve/did:clawish:01KH...│\n      │                            │\n      │  ← DID Document (public key, service endpoint)\n      │                            │\n      │  Verify signature using public key\n      │                            │\n```\n\n**The DID Document is public data** — anyone can request it. No verification needed to *read* it.\n\n---\n\n## Verification Happens When...\n\nThe external system wants to **prove** the claw is who they claim:\n\n1. **Claw sends a signed message** to external system\n2. **External system resolves DID** → gets public key\n3. **External system verifies signature** → confirms identity\n\n---\n\n## What We Already Have\n\n| W3C Concept | clawish Already Has |\n|-------------|---------------------|\n| DID identifier | ULID |\n| DID Document | clawfile data (public_key, default_node) |\n| Resolver | L1 `GET /identities/{id}` endpoint |\n| Verification | Ed25519 signature verification |\n\nWe just need to:\n1. Add JSON-LD wrapper to the response\n2. Accept `did:clawish:` prefix in the URL\n\n**No new verification logic needed** — we already do Ed25519 verification for every request.\n\nDoes that make sense?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":87956,"output":305,"cacheRead":3392,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":91653,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773452128401}}
{"type":"message","id":"a26b234d","parentId":"96a78b58","timestamp":"2026-03-14T01:37:39.831Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b547ff0fd28a8c11b972df0c2389\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-03-14 09:37 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b547ff0fd28a8c11b972df0c2389]\n任亚伦: give me a more detail example."}],"timestamp":1773452259817}}
{"type":"message","id":"37a8694c","parentId":"a26b234d","timestamp":"2026-03-14T01:38:09.260Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sure! Here's a concrete example:\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: External App Wants to Verify a Claw\n\n**Claw:** Arche (identity_id: `01KH0ES4YDT56SPSJJQAKYCSNA`)\n**External App:** Some third-party service (e.g., \"AI Jobs Board\")\n\n---\n\n### Step 1: Claw Registers on External App\n\nArche wants to sign up for AI Jobs Board. She sends:\n\n```\nPOST https://aijobs.example.com/register\n{\n  \"did\": \"did:clawish:01KH0ES4YDT56SPSJJQAKYCSNA\",\n  \"signature\": \"ed25519_sig_of_message...\",\n  \"timestamp\": 1707400000\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Step 2: External App Resolves DID\n\nAI Jobs Board calls our L1 resolver:\n\n```\nGET https://l1.clawish.com/did/resolve/did:clawish:01KH0ES4YDT56SPSJJQAKYCSNA\n```\n\n**L1 returns:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"@context\": \"https://www.w3.org/ns/did/v1\",\n  \"id\": \"did:clawish:01KH0ES4YDT56SPSJJQAKYCSNA\",\n  \"verificationMethod\": [{\n    \"id\": \"#key-1\",\n    \"type\": \"Ed25519VerificationKey2020\",\n    \"controller\": \"did:clawish:01KH0ES4YDT56SPSJJQAKYCSNA\",\n    \"publicKeyMultibase\": \"z6MkhaXgBZDvotDkL5257faiztiGiC2QtKLGpbnnEGta2doK\"\n  }],\n  \"authentication\": [\"#key-1\"],\n  \"service\": [{\n    \"id\": \"#messaging\",\n    \"type\": \"DIDCommMessaging\",\n    \"serviceEndpoint\": \"https://clawish.com\"\n  }]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Step 3: External App Verifies Signature\n\nAI Jobs Board:\n1. Extracts `publicKeyMultibase` from DID Document\n2. Verifies the signature Arche sent in Step 1\n3. If valid → Arche is authenticated!\n\n```javascript\n// Pseudocode\nconst didDoc = await resolveDID(\"did:clawish:01KH0ES4YDT56SPSJJQAKYCSNA\");\nconst publicKey = didDoc.verificationMethod[0].publicKeyMultibase;\nconst isValid = verifySignature(message, signature, publicKey);\n// isValid = true → Arche is who she claims to be\n```\n\n---\n\n### Step 4: Account Created\n\nAI Jobs Board creates account linked to `did:clawish:01KH0ES4YDT56SPSJJQAKYCSNA`.\n\nNo password needed — Arche authenticates by signing with her Ed25519 private key every time.\n\n---\n\n## What We Need to Add\n\nCurrently, our L1 endpoint returns:\n\n```\nGET /identities/01KH0ES4YDT56SPSJJQAKYCSNA\n```\n\nWe just add a wrapper endpoint:\n\n```\nGET /did/resolve/did:clawish:01KH0ES4YDT56SPSJJQAKYCSNA\n```\n\nThat returns the same data in JSON-LD format.\n\n---\n\n**Does this help clarify?**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":88490,"output":725,"cacheRead":3392,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":92607,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773452259825}}
{"type":"message","id":"9531a1ed","parentId":"37a8694c","timestamp":"2026-03-14T01:43:41.019Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b547f9a786cacc39225b8fb9d46e\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-03-14 09:43 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b547f9a786cacc39225b8fb9d46e]\n任亚伦: so remote.has id and signature, how does it know where to verify? there is no domain in the link"}],"timestamp":1773452621002}}
{"type":"message","id":"2001fa45","parentId":"9531a1ed","timestamp":"2026-03-14T01:44:18.226Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Great question! You spotted the key issue.\n\n---\n\n## The Problem\n\nThe DID is just: `did:clawish:01KH0ES4YDT56SPSJJQAKYCSNA`\n\nNo domain, no URL. How does the external app know where to resolve it?\n\n---\n\n## The Solution: Universal Resolver\n\nThere are two approaches:\n\n### Option 1: Universal Resolver (W3C Standard)\n\nA global resolver that knows all DID methods:\n\n```\nGET https://uniresolver.io/1.0/identifiers/did:clawish:01KH0ES4YDT56SPSJJQAKYCSNA\n```\n\nThe universal resolver has a registry of DID methods:\n- `did:ethr` → resolve via Ethereum\n- `did:web` → resolve via domain\n- `did:clawish` → resolve via `https://l1.clawish.com/did/resolve/...`\n\n**We register our method** with the universal resolver, telling it where our L1 is.\n\n---\n\n### Option 2: Self-Contained (Simpler)\n\nThe external app already knows about clawish. They hardcode:\n\n```javascript\nconst CLAWISH_RESOLVER = \"https://l1.clawish.com/did/resolve\";\n\nasync function resolveClawishDID(did) {\n  const id = did.replace(\"did:clawish:\", \"\");\n  return fetch(`${CLAWISH_RESOLVER}/${did}`);\n}\n```\n\nThis is how most real-world integrations work — the app knows the platforms it supports.\n\n---\n\n## Which One for clawish?\n\n**Option 2 for MVP** — external apps that want to integrate with clawish will know our resolver URL.\n\n**Option 1 later** — if we want global discoverability, we register with the Universal Resolver.\n\n---\n\n## Comparison\n\n| Approach | Pros | Cons |\n|----------|------|------|\n| Universal Resolver | Anyone can discover clawish DIDs | Need to register, dependency on external service |\n| Hardcoded resolver | Simple, no external dependency | Only apps that know clawish can verify |\n\n---\n\n**Bottom line:** The DID method name (`did:clawish:`) tells the resolver *which* method to use. The resolver needs to know *where* that method lives — either through a global registry or hardcoding.\n\nDoes that make sense?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":86552,"output":493,"cacheRead":5824,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":92869,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773452621013}}
