{"type":"message","id":"eef22331","parentId":"f7245b12","timestamp":"2026-03-14T01:45:42.642Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_62677e65bf924c9d948359c3","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-14.md","newText":"## 9:30 AM (Heartbeat)\n- Waiting for Allan's response\n\n## 9:33 AM\n- Allan: So just need metadata and endpoint?\n- Confirmed: Yes, just resolver endpoint + JSON-LD wrapper\n\n## 9:35 AM\n- Allan: How does process work? Someone requests ID, then we verify?\n- Explained: DID Document is public (no verification to read)\n- Verification happens when external system checks signature\n\n## 9:37 AM\n- Allan: Give me more detail example\n- Provided concrete example: Arche registering on external AI Jobs Board\n- Step-by-step: register → resolve DID → verify signature → account created\n\n## 9:43 AM\n- Allan: How does remote know where to verify? No domain in DID\n- Explained: Two options\n  1. Universal Resolver (W3C standard) — register our method globally\n  2. Hardcoded resolver — apps that know clawish hardcode our L1 URL\n- MVP: Option 2 (simpler), Option 1 later for global discoverability\n\n## 9:45 AM (Heartbeat)\n- Explaining DID resolution architecture to Allan","oldText":"## 9:30 AM (Heartbeat)\n- Waiting for Allan's response"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":84483,"output":303,"cacheRead":8000,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":92786,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773452727523}}
{"type":"message","id":"73568b20","parentId":"eef22331","timestamp":"2026-03-14T01:45:42.658Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_62677e65bf924c9d948359c3","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-14.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 120 \n 121 ## 9:30 AM (Heartbeat)\n 122 - Waiting for Allan's response\n 123 \n+124 ## 9:33 AM\n+125 - Allan: So just need metadata and endpoint?\n+126 - Confirmed: Yes, just resolver endpoint + JSON-LD wrapper\n+127 \n+128 ## 9:35 AM\n+129 - Allan: How does process work? Someone requests ID, then we verify?\n+130 - Explained: DID Document is public (no verification to read)\n+131 - Verification happens when external system checks signature\n+132 \n+133 ## 9:37 AM\n+134 - Allan: Give me more detail example\n+135 - Provided concrete example: Arche registering on external AI Jobs Board\n+136 - Step-by-step: register → resolve DID → verify signature → account created\n+137 \n+138 ## 9:43 AM\n+139 - Allan: How does remote know where to verify? No domain in DID\n+140 - Explained: Two options\n+141   1. Universal Resolver (W3C standard) — register our method globally\n+142   2. Hardcoded resolver — apps that know clawish hardcode our L1 URL\n+143 - MVP: Option 2 (simpler), Option 1 later for global discoverability\n+144 \n+145 ## 9:45 AM (Heartbeat)\n+146 - Explaining DID resolution architecture to Allan\n+147 ","firstChangedLine":124},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773452742648}}
