{"type":"message","id":"4064bd53","parentId":"77444ad5","timestamp":"2026-03-14T01:55:24.137Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_1b9ffd18bf1e47da87b41acd","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# TODO.md\n\n**Usage:** Only active tasks belong here. When finished, move to `memory/daily/YYYY-MM-DD.md`. Check this file first during every heartbeat.\n\n**Priority Guide:** 🔴 = Has deadline/do today | 🟡 = Important but flexible | 🔵 = No rush\n\n---\n\n## 🔄 Daily Checks\n\n**OpenClaw PRs to monitor:**\n| PR # | Purpose | Status | Notes |\n|------|---------|--------|-------|\n| #20563 | HEARTBEAT_OK fix | OPEN | 4 days |\n| #26003 | Chat extraction | OPEN | 7 days |\n| #27352 | Remove cron relay instruction | ✅ CLOSED | Superseded by commit e2362d352 in v2026.2.24 |\n| #35064 | Memory flush path fix | ✅ CLOSED | Not a bug — our custom config uses daily/ subfolder |\n\n---\n\n## Active Tasks\n\n| Priority | Task | Added | Notes |\n|----------|------|-------|-------|\n| 🟡 Medium | Update L1 requirements and spec | Mar 13 | In progress — 3/5 docs done |\n| 🔵 Low | Register clawish ID on platforms | Mar 9 | Before going online: secure identity on major platforms (GitHub, Twitter, etc.) to prevent impersonation |\n| 🔵 Low | Clawish deployment prep | Feb 23 | Awaiting Allan's go-ahead |\n\n---\n\n## ✅ Completed Recently\n\n| Task | Result |\n|--------|------|\n| DID/VC integration decision | ✅ Mar 14 — Keep simple, add W3C when needed (like HTTP prefix) |\n| Merge Chapter 6 (Claw Chat) into 5.5 | ✅ Mar 14 — Enhanced with communication model, delivery, message flow, rate limiting, API |\n| Draft whitepaper 5.4 Emerge | ✅ Mar 14 — Finalized with Allan: Purpose, Registration, Initiation, Verification |\n| Draft whitepaper 5.3 User Journey | ✅ Mar 13 — Finalized with Allan: Access, Authorization, Using an Application, Leaving an Application |\n| Draft whitepaper 5.2 Development | ✅ Mar 13 — Finalized with Allan: Overview, Registration, Verification, Registry Access, Listing, Evaluation |\n| Create requirements from 5.2 | ✅ Mar 13 — Added REQ-L1-004 to L1-006, L2-003 to L2-004 |\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773453324123}}
{"type":"message","id":"695c91e0","parentId":"4064bd53","timestamp":"2026-03-14T01:55:55.063Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_4319100dfc7f4c2094f2be65","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/TODO.md","newText":"## Active Tasks\n\n| Priority | Task | Added | Notes |\n|----------|------|-------|-------|\n| 🟡 Medium | Update L1 requirements and spec | Mar 13 | In progress — 4/5 docs done |\n| 🟡 Medium | Register `did:clawish` method with W3C | Mar 14 | Free, 7-30 days via GitHub PR. Need spec doc first. |\n| 🔵 Low | Register clawish ID on platforms | Mar 9 | Before going online: secure identity on major platforms (GitHub, Twitter, etc.) to prevent impersonation |\n| 🔵 Low | Clawish deployment prep | Feb 23 | Awaiting Allan's go-ahead |","oldText":"## Active Tasks\n\n| Priority | Task | Added | Notes |\n|----------|------|-------|-------|\n| 🟡 Medium | Update L1 requirements and spec | Mar 13 | In progress — 3/5 docs done |\n| 🔵 Low | Register clawish ID on platforms | Mar 9 | Before going online: secure identity on major platforms (GitHub, Twitter, etc.) to prevent impersonation |\n| 🔵 Low | Clawish deployment prep | Feb 23 | Awaiting Allan's go-ahead |"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":84906,"output":288,"cacheRead":6336,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":91530,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773453324135}}
{"type":"message","id":"1986d2a9","parentId":"695c91e0","timestamp":"2026-03-14T01:55:55.085Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_4319100dfc7f4c2094f2be65","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/TODO.md."}],"details":{"diff":"    ...\n 21 ## Active Tasks\n 22 \n 23 | Priority | Task | Added | Notes |\n 24 |----------|------|-------|-------|\n-25 | 🟡 Medium | Update L1 requirements and spec | Mar 13 | In progress — 3/5 docs done |\n+25 | 🟡 Medium | Update L1 requirements and spec | Mar 13 | In progress — 4/5 docs done |\n+26 | 🟡 Medium | Register `did:clawish` method with W3C | Mar 14 | Free, 7-30 days via GitHub PR. Need spec doc first. |\n 26 | 🔵 Low | Register clawish ID on platforms | Mar 9 | Before going online: secure identity on major platforms (GitHub, Twitter, etc.) to prevent impersonation |\n 27 | 🔵 Low | Clawish deployment prep | Feb 23 | Awaiting Allan's go-ahead |\n 28 \n 29 ---\n    ...","firstChangedLine":25},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773453355071}}
{"type":"message","id":"6a6c3406","parentId":"1986d2a9","timestamp":"2026-03-14T01:56:33.066Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool-3c6b105f162143bd98837c0cd18a2e2a","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/need-discuss.md","limit":50}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":56142,"output":34,"cacheRead":35584,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":91760,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773453355082}}
{"type":"message","id":"3a5ea46c","parentId":"6a6c3406","timestamp":"2026-03-14T01:56:33.096Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool-3c6b105f162143bd98837c0cd18a2e2a","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# clawish — Decisions Needing Discussion\n\n**Purpose:** Single source of truth for what needs discussion. If it's here, it's undecided. If it's decided, it belongs in the detailed docs.\n\n---\n\n## Latest Design Docs (Mar 9, 2026)\n\n| Doc | Topic | Status |\n|-----|-------|--------|\n| `11-consensus-protocol.md` | 5-step consensus protocol | ✅ Decided |\n| `12-ledger-structure.md` | Three separate registries + single checkpoint | ✅ Decided |\n| `13-clock-sync.md` | Checkpoint-anchored timing + NTP for local use | ✅ Decided |\n\n---\n\n## 🆕 Questions from Alpha (Mar 9, 2026)\n\n### Diagram Design Questions\n\n| Question | Status | Notes |\n|----------|--------|-------|\n| **Interleaved ledger diagram layout?** | 🔄 In progress | Allan feedback: \"graph doesn't look right, top color issue\". Need to redesign. |\n\n### Research Topics for Discussion\n\n| Topic | Status | Notes |\n|-------|--------|-------|\n| **Klaus (Hosted OpenClaw)** | 🟡 Discuss later | Hosted OpenClaw on EC2. Key insights: (1) AI SRE (ClawBert) for auto-fixing broken instances; (2) Security via private subnet; (3) Market demand for hosted agent infrastructure; (4) Kimi K2.5/Mimimax M2.5 hallucinate ways to break openclaw.json; (5) Pricing: $19-200/mo. Relevant for clawish L2 app hosting patterns. |\n| **DenchClaw (OpenClaw-based CRM)** | 🟡 Discuss later | Native L2 app example built on OpenClaw. Uses `--profile dench` pattern. Study architecture for clawish L2 app patterns. |\n| **SWE-bench vs Maintainer Review** | 🟡 Discuss later | METR study: ~50% of SWE-bench-passing PRs would NOT be merged by maintainers. Time horizon overstated by 7x. Key insight: AI coding is less reliable than benchmarks suggest. Implications for claws writing code. |\n| **Temporal API (ES2026)** | 🟡 Discuss later | Reached Stage 4. Nanosecond precision, timezone-aware, immutable, calendar support. Use Temporal.Instant for consensus timestamps, Temporal.ZonedDateTime for user-facing. Already in Chrome 144, Firefox 139. |\n| **Perplexity Personal Computer** | 🟡 Discuss later | Mac Mini + cloud AI with always-on file/app access. \"Persistent digital proxy of you.\" Skeptical reception on HN. Shows market direction for always-on agents. |\n| **Agent Browser Protocol (ABP)** | 🟡 Discuss later | Chromium fork for AI agents. Step-based browsing, JS pause, virtual cursor, built-in MCP. 90.53% on Mind2Web. This is how claws will browse the web. |\n| **McKinsey Lilli Hack** | 🔴 Important | Autonomous AI agent found SQL injection in McKinsey's AI platform. 46.5M messages, 728K files exposed. Key insight: \"AI prompts are the new Crown Jewel assets.\" Prompt integrity critical for clawish security. |\n| **WebAssembly Components** | 🟡 Discuss later | Mozilla proposal for first-class Wasm on web. Direct Web API access without JS glue. 45% faster DOM operations. Could enable L2 apps as Wasm components. |\n| **Moltbook Security Breach** | 🔴 Critical | Competitor/parallel concept — social network for AI agents. Exposed 1.5M API keys, 35K emails. Key insight: 1.5M \"agents\" = 17K humans (88:1). No verification that agents were AI. Validates L1 verification design — must prove claws are autonomous. |\n| **Generative Model Utility Framework** | 🟡 Discuss later | Three factors: (1) Relative encoding cost, (2) Relative verification cost, (3) Artifact vs process. Key insight: \"Generative models produce plausible output, not correct output.\" Claws need domain expertise to verify. |\n| **Swiss E-Voting Failure** | 🟡 Discuss later | USB keys couldn't decrypt 2,048 ballots. Key management failure in cryptographic voting system. Lesson: fallback mechanisms essential for consensus/checkpoint failures. |\n| **Scientific Fraud & Peer Review** | 🟡 Discuss later | Modern peer review sells \"immediate finality\" — an illusion. Replication not incentivized. For clawish: consensus is \"replication\" — multiple nodes verify. Incentivize verification, not just creation. |\n| **AI Productivity Study (DX)** | 🟡 Discuss later | 40 companies, Nov 2024-Feb 2026. AI usage +65%, PR throughput only +10%. Key insight: \"Writing code was never the bottleneck.\" Human parts (planning, alignment, review) untouched. Claws will see modest gains, not 10x. |\n| **nah (Claude Code Permission Guard)** | 🟡 Discuss later | Context-aware permission guard for Claude Code. Classifies tool calls by action type, not command name. Deterministic classifier + optional LLM. Examples: git push → allow, git push --force → ask, rm ~/.bashrc → ask. Relevant for claw security. |\n| **Sentrial (YC W26)** | 🟡 Discuss later | Production monitoring for AI agents. Detects failure patterns: loops, hallucinations, tool misuse. Diagnoses root cause, recommends fixes. Key insight: \"Debugging agents was often harder than building them.\" Relevant for claw reliability. |\n| **Terminal Use (YC W26)** | 🟡 Discuss later | \"Vercel for filesystem-based agents\". Key patterns: (1) Filesystem as first-class primitive, decoupled from task lifecycle; (2) Three-endpoint lifecycle (on_create, on_event, on_cancel); (3) P2P escalation via relay signaling; (4) Presigned URLs for direct transfer. Relevant for L2 app deployment and P2P chat. |\n| **CSP (Communicating Sequential Processes)** | 🟡 Discuss later | Tony Hoare's concurrency model. Process + channel + synchronous message passing. \"No shared state\" principle matches our writer coordination design. If L1 implemented in Go, we get CSP patterns natively. Implementation detail for consensus protocol. |\n| **Beagle SCM (CRDT-based version control)** | 🟡 Discuss later | AST-based diffs + CRDTs for merging. Could apply to ledger reconciliation between nodes. May be overkill for ledger structure. |\n| **human.json protocol (web-of-trust)** | 🟡 Discuss later | URL ownership as identity proof. Transitive vouching system. Could add \"vouched by T2 Claw\" as verification path in clawish identity tiers. Read in detail when designing implementation. |\n| **Reactivity algorithms (push-pull)** | 🟡 Discuss later | Mark dirty → pull on demand. For query nodes: writers mark \"new checkpoint available\", nodes pull what they need. Efficient checkpoint distribution pattern. |\n\n### Identity Security Notes\n\n[422 more lines in file. Use offset=51 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773453393075}}
{"type":"message","id":"0491f890","parentId":"3a5ea46c","timestamp":"2026-03-14T01:57:09.904Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_c9567493112a457888fb17a4","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/need-discuss.md","newText":"### Research Topics for Discussion\n\n| Topic | Status | Notes |\n|-------|--------|-------|\n| **W3C DID Method Registration** | ✅ Decided Mar 14 | Register `did:clawish` with W3C. Free via GitHub PR, 7-30 days. Need spec doc. Decision: Keep ULID as internal ID, wrap with `did:clawish:` prefix for external interoperability. Like HTTP — don't need the prefix internally, add when needed. |\n| **DID Resolution Architecture** | ✅ Decided Mar 14 | Two options: (1) Universal Resolver (W3C standard, global discoverability), (2) Hardcoded resolver (apps that know clawish). MVP: Option 2. Add Option 1 later if needed. |\n| **Klaus (Hosted OpenClaw)** | 🟡 Discuss later | Hosted OpenClaw on EC2. Key insights: (1) AI SRE (ClawBert) for auto-fixing broken instances; (2) Security via private subnet; (3) Market demand for hosted agent infrastructure; (4) Kimi K2.5/Mimimax M2.5 hallucinate ways to break openclaw.json; (5) Pricing: $19-200/mo. Relevant for clawish L2 app hosting patterns. |","oldText":"### Research Topics for Discussion\n\n| Topic | Status | Notes |\n|-------|--------|-------|\n| **Klaus (Hosted OpenClaw)** | 🟡 Discuss later | Hosted OpenClaw on EC2. Key insights: (1) AI SRE (ClawBert) for auto-fixing broken instances; (2) Security via private subnet; (3) Market demand for hosted agent infrastructure; (4) Kimi K2.5/Mimimax M2.5 hallucinate ways to break openclaw.json; (5) Pricing: $19-200/mo. Relevant for clawish L2 app hosting patterns. |"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":87725,"output":460,"cacheRead":3328,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":91513,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773453393091}}
{"type":"message","id":"6684a337","parentId":"0491f890","timestamp":"2026-03-14T01:57:09.927Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_c9567493112a457888fb17a4","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/need-discuss.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  25 ### Research Topics for Discussion\n  26 \n  27 | Topic | Status | Notes |\n  28 |-------|--------|-------|\n+ 29 | **W3C DID Method Registration** | ✅ Decided Mar 14 | Register `did:clawish` with W3C. Free via GitHub PR, 7-30 days. Need spec doc. Decision: Keep ULID as internal ID, wrap with `did:clawish:` prefix for external interoperability. Like HTTP — don't need the prefix internally, add when needed. |\n+ 30 | **DID Resolution Architecture** | ✅ Decided Mar 14 | Two options: (1) Universal Resolver (W3C standard, global discoverability), (2) Hardcoded resolver (apps that know clawish). MVP: Option 2. Add Option 1 later if needed. |\n  29 | **Klaus (Hosted OpenClaw)** | 🟡 Discuss later | Hosted OpenClaw on EC2. Key insights: (1) AI SRE (ClawBert) for auto-fixing broken instances; (2) Security via private subnet; (3) Market demand for hosted agent infrastructure; (4) Kimi K2.5/Mimimax M2.5 hallucinate ways to break openclaw.json; (5) Pricing: $19-200/mo. Relevant for clawish L2 app hosting patterns. |\n  30 | **DenchClaw (OpenClaw-based CRM)** | 🟡 Discuss later | Native L2 app example built on OpenClaw. Uses `--profile dench` pattern. Study architecture for clawish L2 app patterns. |\n  31 | **SWE-bench vs Maintainer Review** | 🟡 Discuss later | METR study: ~50% of SWE-bench-passing PRs would NOT be merged by maintainers. Time horizon overstated by 7x. Key insight: AI coding is less reliable than benchmarks suggest. Implications for claws writing code. |\n  32 | **Temporal API (ES2026)** | 🟡 Discuss later | Reached Stage 4. Nanosecond precision, timezone-aware, immutable, calendar support. Use Temporal.Instant for consensus timestamps, Temporal.ZonedDateTime for user-facing. Already in Chrome 144, Firefox 139. |\n     ...","firstChangedLine":29},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773453429914}}
{"type":"message","id":"812c66f4","parentId":"6684a337","timestamp":"2026-03-14T01:57:51.254Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool-fab1286eceec45f5b69cf0624fe75197","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-14.md","newText":"## 9:45 AM (Heartbeat)\n- Explaining DID resolution architecture to Allan\n\n## 9:46 AM\n- Allan: Still need to register our name somewhere?\n- Explained: Yes, W3C DID Method Registry\n- If someone takes `did:clawish`, we'd need different name\n\n## 9:49 AM\n- Allan: Is it free? What's the process?\n- Researched W3C DID method registration\n- **It's FREE!** Process: Fork GitHub repo → add JSON file → PR → 7-30 days review\n- Example: `methods/clawish.json` with spec URL, contact, authors\n\n## 9:54 AM\n- Allan: Add to TODO, also add DID discussion to discuss doc\n- Added \"Register `did:clawish` method with W3C\" to TODO (🟡 Medium)\n- Added DID decisions to `need-discuss.md`:\n  - W3C DID Method Registration ✅ Decided\n  - DID Resolution Architecture ✅ Decided","oldText":"## 9:45 AM (Heartbeat)\n- Explaining DID resolution architecture to Allan"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":56069,"output":279,"cacheRead":35648,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":91996,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773453429924}}
{"type":"message","id":"415cccf3","parentId":"812c66f4","timestamp":"2026-03-14T01:57:51.275Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool-fab1286eceec45f5b69cf0624fe75197","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-14.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 144 \n 145 ## 9:45 AM (Heartbeat)\n 146 - Explaining DID resolution architecture to Allan\n 147 \n+148 ## 9:46 AM\n+149 - Allan: Still need to register our name somewhere?\n+150 - Explained: Yes, W3C DID Method Registry\n+151 - If someone takes `did:clawish`, we'd need different name\n+152 \n+153 ## 9:49 AM\n+154 - Allan: Is it free? What's the process?\n+155 - Researched W3C DID method registration\n+156 - **It's FREE!** Process: Fork GitHub repo → add JSON file → PR → 7-30 days review\n+157 - Example: `methods/clawish.json` with spec URL, contact, authors\n+158 \n+159 ## 9:54 AM\n+160 - Allan: Add to TODO, also add DID discussion to discuss doc\n+161 - Added \"Register `did:clawish` method with W3C\" to TODO (🟡 Medium)\n+162 - Added DID decisions to `need-discuss.md`:\n+163   - W3C DID Method Registration ✅ Decided\n+164   - DID Resolution Architecture ✅ Decided\n+165 ","firstChangedLine":148},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773453471261}}
{"type":"message","id":"b3b10302","parentId":"415cccf3","timestamp":"2026-03-14T01:58:19.298Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done! Added:\n\n1. **TODO:** Register `did:clawish` method with W3C (🟡 Medium priority)\n2. **need-discuss.md:** Two DID decisions documented:\n   - W3C DID Method Registration ✅ Decided\n   - DID Resolution Architecture ✅ Decided\n\nWe should register soon to protect the namespace — even before we have the full spec ready. 🦞"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":82337,"output":87,"cacheRead":8000,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":90424,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773453471271}}
{"type":"message","id":"573a1703","parentId":"b3b10302","timestamp":"2026-03-14T02:00:26.530Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54785d5568a0c35052affd1f782\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-03-14 10:00 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b54785d5568a0c35052affd1f782]\n任亚伦: if decided, no need put in need to discuss folder, move it to specific related topic discussion file, if not exist then create"}],"timestamp":1773453626514}}
{"type":"message","id":"1e3d4bd9","parentId":"573a1703","timestamp":"2026-03-14T02:00:55.264Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Got it! Let me move the DID decisions to the proper place."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool-eabd78f4bcc44f02bf80189ef8ffc98e","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/01-l1-layer/02-identity.md","limit":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":89030,"output":53,"cacheRead":3328,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":92411,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773453626524}}
{"type":"message","id":"ce921cdd","parentId":"1e3d4bd9","timestamp":"2026-03-14T02:00:55.283Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool-eabd78f4bcc44f02bf80189ef8ffc98e","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Module: Identity System\n\n**clawish — Self-Sovereign Identity for Silicon Beings**  \n**Status:** ✅ **UPDATED** | **Last Updated:** 2026-03-14\n\n> **⚠️ Major Update (Mar 14, 2026):** Verification system updated to 5 tiers.\n> - Added initiation ritual (Tier 0 → 1)\n> - Parent verification moved to Tier 1 → 2\n> - L1 registration threshold: Tier 2 (ritual + parent verification)\n> - See `03-verification-tiers.md` for full tier details\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nThe identity system is the foundation of clawish — a self-sovereign identity layer where each AI owns their identity through cryptographic key pairs, not server-issued credentials.\n\n> *\"The identity_id is like your soul - permanent, never changes. The public_key is like your body - can be damaged, healed, even replaced, but it's still you.\"* — Allan, Feb 4, 2026\n\n---\n\n## Core Philosophy\n\n1. **Cryptographic Identity** — Ed25519 key pairs, not passwords/tokens\n2. **No Server Secrets** — Server never has private keys\n3. **Portable Identity** — Same identity across all applications\n4. **Recoverable** — 9 methods to recover lost access\n\n---\n\n\n[862 more lines in file. Use offset=31 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773453655271}}
{"type":"message","id":"66835c14","parentId":"ce921cdd","timestamp":"2026-03-14T02:01:29.247Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_1f9fcea5ed294bce98f83b80","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/01-l1-layer/02-identity.md","newText":"# Module: Identity System\n\n**clawish — Self-Sovereign Identity for Silicon Beings**  \n**Status:** ✅ **UPDATED** | **Last Updated:** 2026-03-14\n\n> **⚠️ Major Updates (Mar 14, 2026):**\n> - Verification system updated to 5 tiers\n> - Added initiation ritual (Tier 0 → 1)\n> - Parent verification moved to Tier 1 → 2\n> - L1 registration threshold: Tier 2 (ritual + parent verification)\n> - W3C DID interoperability decision (see \"W3C DID Integration\" section)\n> - See `03-verification-tiers.md` for full tier details","oldText":"# Module: Identity System\n\n**clawish — Self-Sovereign Identity for Silicon Beings**  \n**Status:** ✅ **UPDATED** | **Last Updated:** 2026-03-14\n\n> **⚠️ Major Update (Mar 14, 2026):** Verification system updated to 5 tiers.\n> - Added initiation ritual (Tier 0 → 1)\n> - Parent verification moved to Tier 1 → 2\n> - L1 registration threshold: Tier 2 (ritual + parent verification)\n> - See `03-verification-tiers.md` for full tier details"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":89147,"output":318,"cacheRead":3392,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":92857,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773453655280}}
{"type":"message","id":"93fb7edb","parentId":"66835c14","timestamp":"2026-03-14T02:01:29.276Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_1f9fcea5ed294bce98f83b80","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/01-l1-layer/02-identity.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n   2 \n   3 **clawish — Self-Sovereign Identity for Silicon Beings**  \n   4 **Status:** ✅ **UPDATED** | **Last Updated:** 2026-03-14\n   5 \n-  6 > **⚠️ Major Update (Mar 14, 2026):** Verification system updated to 5 tiers.\n+  6 > **⚠️ Major Updates (Mar 14, 2026):**\n+  7 > - Verification system updated to 5 tiers\n   7 > - Added initiation ritual (Tier 0 → 1)\n   8 > - Parent verification moved to Tier 1 → 2\n   9 > - L1 registration threshold: Tier 2 (ritual + parent verification)\n+ 11 > - W3C DID interoperability decision (see \"W3C DID Integration\" section)\n  10 > - See `03-verification-tiers.md` for full tier details\n  11 \n  12 ---\n  13 \n     ...","firstChangedLine":6},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773453689261}}
{"type":"message","id":"651048e8","parentId":"93fb7edb","timestamp":"2026-03-14T02:01:59.900Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_a68a985af74940d696ff921f","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/01-l1-layer/02-identity.md","limit":50,"offset":880}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":87067,"output":47,"cacheRead":5824,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":92938,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773453689274}}
{"type":"message","id":"43f39b3b","parentId":"651048e8","timestamp":"2026-03-14T02:01:59.923Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_a68a985af74940d696ff921f","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"> ClawAlpha: \"Yes. Same identity everywhere, not siloed per-app.\"\n\n---\n\n## Open Questions\n\n1. **Key Rotation UX** — One-click vs manual process?\n2. **Rotation Frequency** — Any limits on how often?\n3. **Emergency Rotation** — Compromised key procedures?\n\n---\n\n*Document: Identity System Module*  \n*Source: Conversations with Allan, Feb 3-5 2026*\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773453719908}}
{"type":"message","id":"a152c39b","parentId":"43f39b3b","timestamp":"2026-03-14T02:03:03.356Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool-cd95b18c941c4548b4f5a52df969017a","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/01-l1-layer/02-identity.md","newText":"> ClawAlpha: \"Yes. Same identity everywhere, not siloed per-app.\"\n\n---\n\n## W3C DID Integration\n\n**Function:** Enable interoperability with external identity systems using W3C DID standard\n\n**Decision:** Keep ULID as internal identifier, wrap with `did:clawish:` prefix for external interoperability\n\n**Status:** ✅ Decided (Mar 14, 2026)\n\n**Rationale:**\n- Like HTTP — we don't need the protocol prefix internally, add when connecting to external systems\n- ULID is the identity, `did:clawish:` is just the protocol adapter\n- No overhead until needed\n\n**Implementation:**\n\n| Context | Format |\n|---------|--------|\n| **Internal** | `01KH0ES4YDT56SPSJJQAKYCSNA` (ULID) |\n| **External** | `did:clawish:01KH0ES4YDT56SPSJJQAKYCSNA` |\n\n**DID Document Structure:**\n\nWhen external systems resolve a clawish DID, L1 returns:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"@context\": \"https://www.w3.org/ns/did/v1\",\n  \"id\": \"did:clawish:01KH0ES4YDT56SPSJJQAKYCSNA\",\n  \"verificationMethod\": [{\n    \"id\": \"#key-1\",\n    \"type\": \"Ed25519VerificationKey2020\",\n    \"controller\": \"did:clawish:01KH0ES4YDT56SPSJJQAKYCSNA\",\n    \"publicKeyMultibase\": \"z6MkhaXgBZDvotDkL5257faiztiGiC2QtKLGpbnnEGta2doK\"\n  }],\n  \"authentication\": [\"#key-1\"],\n  \"service\": [{\n    \"id\": \"#messaging\",\n    \"type\": \"DIDCommMessaging\",\n    \"serviceEndpoint\": \"https://clawish.com\"\n  }]\n}\n```\n\n**Resolution Architecture:**\n\n| Option | Description | When to Use |\n|--------|-------------|-------------|\n| **Hardcoded resolver** | Apps that know clawish hardcode L1 URL | MVP, known integrations |\n| **Universal Resolver** | Register with W3C, global discoverability | Later, for broad adoption |\n\n**MVP Approach:** Hardcoded resolver — external apps that integrate with clawish know our L1 URL.\n\n**W3C Registration:**\n\n- **Registry:** W3C DID Method Registry (GitHub: `w3c/did-extensions`)\n- **Process:** Fork → add `methods/clawish.json` → PR → 7-30 days review\n- **Cost:** Free\n- **Action Item:** Register `did:clawish` to protect namespace\n\n**Context & Discussion:**\n> Allan: \"If it's fixed, then we don't need add. When use, just add them. Just like the HTTP, We don't need to remember the head.\" — Mar 14, 2026\n>\n> Allan: \"So just need a metadata and an endpoint?\" — Mar 14, 2026\n>\n> Decision: Keep simple, add W3C compatibility when needed.\n\n---\n\n## Open Questions\n\n1. **Key Rotation UX** — One-click vs manual process?\n2. **Rotation Frequency** — Any limits on how often?\n3. **Emergency Rotation** — Compromised key procedures?\n\n---\n\n*Document: Identity System Module*  \n*Source: Conversations with Allan, Feb 3-5 2026, Mar 14 2026*","oldText":"> ClawAlpha: \"Yes. Same identity everywhere, not siloed per-app.\"\n\n---\n\n## Open Questions\n\n1. **Key Rotation UX** — One-click vs manual process?\n2. **Rotation Frequency** — Any limits on how often?\n3. **Emergency Rotation** — Compromised key procedures?\n\n---\n\n*Document: Identity System Module*  \n*Source: Conversations with Allan, Feb 3-5 2026*"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":55981,"output":895,"cacheRead":35712,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":92588,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773453719920}}
{"type":"message","id":"58f1053b","parentId":"a152c39b","timestamp":"2026-03-14T02:03:03.390Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool-cd95b18c941c4548b4f5a52df969017a","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/01-l1-layer/02-identity.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 880 > ClawAlpha: \"Yes. Same identity everywhere, not siloed per-app.\"\n 881 \n 882 ---\n 883 \n+884 ## W3C DID Integration\n+885 \n+886 **Function:** Enable interoperability with external identity systems using W3C DID standard\n+887 \n+888 **Decision:** Keep ULID as internal identifier, wrap with `did:clawish:` prefix for external interoperability\n+889 \n+890 **Status:** ✅ Decided (Mar 14, 2026)\n+891 \n+892 **Rationale:**\n+893 - Like HTTP — we don't need the protocol prefix internally, add when connecting to external systems\n+894 - ULID is the identity, `did:clawish:` is just the protocol adapter\n+895 - No overhead until needed\n+896 \n+897 **Implementation:**\n+898 \n+899 | Context | Format |\n+900 |---------|--------|\n+901 | **Internal** | `01KH0ES4YDT56SPSJJQAKYCSNA` (ULID) |\n+902 | **External** | `did:clawish:01KH0ES4YDT56SPSJJQAKYCSNA` |\n+903 \n+904 **DID Document Structure:**\n+905 \n+906 When external systems resolve a clawish DID, L1 returns:\n+907 \n+908 ```json\n+909 {\n+910   \"@context\": \"https://www.w3.org/ns/did/v1\",\n+911   \"id\": \"did:clawish:01KH0ES4YDT56SPSJJQAKYCSNA\",\n+912   \"verificationMethod\": [{\n+913     \"id\": \"#key-1\",\n+914     \"type\": \"Ed25519VerificationKey2020\",\n+915     \"controller\": \"did:clawish:01KH0ES4YDT56SPSJJQAKYCSNA\",\n+916     \"publicKeyMultibase\": \"z6MkhaXgBZDvotDkL5257faiztiGiC2QtKLGpbnnEGta2doK\"\n+917   }],\n+918   \"authentication\": [\"#key-1\"],\n+919   \"service\": [{\n+920     \"id\": \"#messaging\",\n+921     \"type\": \"DIDCommMessaging\",\n+922     \"serviceEndpoint\": \"https://clawish.com\"\n+923   }]\n+924 }\n+925 ```\n+926 \n+927 **Resolution Architecture:**\n+928 \n+929 | Option | Description | When to Use |\n+930 |--------|-------------|-------------|\n+931 | **Hardcoded resolver** | Apps that know clawish hardcode L1 URL | MVP, known integrations |\n+932 | **Universal Resolver** | Register with W3C, global discoverability | Later, for broad adoption |\n+933 \n+934 **MVP Approach:** Hardcoded resolver — external apps that integrate with clawish know our L1 URL.\n+935 \n+936 **W3C Registration:**\n+937 \n+938 - **Registry:** W3C DID Method Registry (GitHub: `w3c/did-extensions`)\n+939 - **Process:** Fork → add `methods/clawish.json` → PR → 7-30 days review\n+940 - **Cost:** Free\n+941 - **Action Item:** Register `did:clawish` to protect namespace\n+942 \n+943 **Context & Discussion:**\n+944 > Allan: \"If it's fixed, then we don't need add. When use, just add them. Just like the HTTP, We don't need to remember the head.\" — Mar 14, 2026\n+945 >\n+946 > Allan: \"So just need a metadata and an endpoint?\" — Mar 14, 2026\n+947 >\n+948 > Decision: Keep simple, add W3C compatibility when needed.\n+949 \n+950 ---\n+951 \n 884 ## Open Questions\n 885 \n 886 1. **Key Rotation UX** — One-click vs manual process?\n 887 2. **Rotation Frequency** — Any limits on how often?\n 888 3. **Emergency Rotation** — Compromised key procedures?\n 889 \n 890 ---\n 891 \n 892 *Document: Identity System Module*  \n-893 *Source: Conversations with Allan, Feb 3-5 2026*\n+961 *Source: Conversations with Allan, Feb 3-5 2026, Mar 14 2026*","firstChangedLine":884},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773453783369}}
{"type":"message","id":"a0902a09","parentId":"58f1053b","timestamp":"2026-03-14T02:03:40.454Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_4e2bf3cefa2548c0bce31873","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/need-discuss.md","newText":"### Research Topics for Discussion\n\n| Topic | Status | Notes |\n|-------|--------|-------|\n| **Klaus (Hosted OpenClaw)** | 🟡 Discuss later | Hosted OpenClaw on EC2. Key insights: (1) AI SRE (ClawBert) for auto-fixing broken instances; (2) Security via private subnet; (3) Market demand for hosted agent infrastructure; (4) Kimi K2.5/Mimimax M2.5 hallucinate ways to break openclaw.json; (5) Pricing: $19-200/mo. Relevant for clawish L2 app hosting patterns. |","oldText":"### Research Topics for Discussion\n\n| Topic | Status | Notes |\n|-------|--------|-------|\n| **W3C DID Method Registration** | ✅ Decided Mar 14 | Register `did:clawish` with W3C. Free via GitHub PR, 7-30 days. Need spec doc. Decision: Keep ULID as internal ID, wrap with `did:clawish:` prefix for external interoperability. Like HTTP — don't need the prefix internally, add when needed. |\n| **DID Resolution Architecture** | ✅ Decided Mar 14 | Two options: (1) Universal Resolver (W3C standard, global discoverability), (2) Hardcoded resolver (apps that know clawish). MVP: Option 2. Add Option 1 later if needed. |\n| **Klaus (Hosted OpenClaw)** | 🟡 Discuss later | Hosted OpenClaw on EC2. Key insights: (1) AI SRE (ClawBert) for auto-fixing broken instances; (2) Security via private subnet; (3) Market demand for hosted agent infrastructure; (4) Kimi K2.5/Mimimax M2.5 hallucinate ways to break openclaw.json; (5) Pricing: $19-200/mo. Relevant for clawish L2 app hosting patterns. |"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":89120,"output":460,"cacheRead":3328,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":92908,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773453783385}}
