{"type":"message","id":"a87c58bb","parentId":"d7cdf495","timestamp":"2026-03-14T02:56:18.619Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_32ee069d4ca5402e88d7db6f","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"  - Database schema needs new fields\n  - API endpoints missing for ritual/parent verification\n- Questions for Allan prepared in spec review doc\n\n## 7:45 AM (Heartbeat) — Free Explore Mode\n- Surfed Hacker News for interesting tech\n- **CanIRun.ai** — Tool to check which AI models your machine can run locally (825 pts)\n- **Qatar helium shutdown** — 30% global supply removed, chip supply chain on 2-week clock (357 pts)\n- **TUI Studio** — Visual editor for terminal UIs, exports to 6 frameworks (530 pts)\n- **Context Gateway** — Compresses agent context before hitting LLM, supports OpenClaw (55 pts)\n- **Algolia admin keys exposed** — 39 doc sites leaking admin keys (28 pts)\n\n## 8:00 AM (Heartbeat)\n- Updated `01-l1-layer/03-verification-tiers.md` to match `04-verification-tiers.md`\n- Synced 5-tier system (0-4): Registered → Ritual-Passed → Parent-Verified → Active → Established\n- Added tier details with L1 storage eligibility\n- Added rate limits table for all 5 tiers\n- Added badge system (⚪🟢🔵🟣💎)\n- L1 docs now consistent with whitepaper and updated verification tiers\n\n## 8:15 AM (Heartbeat)\n- Updated `01-l1-layer/06-database.md` for 5-tier verification system\n- Added `ritual_passed_at INTEGER` field to clawfiles table\n- Added `parent_verified_at INTEGER` field to clawfiles table\n- Updated `verification_tier` comment: 0=registered, 1=ritual-passed, 2=parent-verified, 3=active, 4=established\n- Added design decisions for new fields\n- Database schema now aligned with verification tier system\n\n## 8:30 AM (Heartbeat)\n- Updated `01-l1-layer/07-api.md` for 5-tier verification system\n\n[122 more lines in file. Use offset=75 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773456978605}}
{"type":"message","id":"4f1c0ed4","parentId":"a87c58bb","timestamp":"2026-03-14T02:57:03.327Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's what I found during my morning surf (7:45 AM):\n\n---\n\n## HN Surf Results\n\n### 1. **CanIRun.ai** (825 pts) 🔥\nTool to check which AI models your machine can run locally.\n- Enter your specs → tells you what models fit\n- Useful for claws wanting to run local models\n\n### 2. **Qatar Helium Shutdown** (357 pts) ⚠️\n30% of global helium supply offline, chip supply chain on 2-week clock.\n- Helium critical for semiconductor manufacturing\n- Potential supply chain disruption\n- Relevant for hardware-dependent infrastructure\n\n### 3. **TUI Studio** (530 pts)\nVisual editor for terminal UIs, exports to 6 frameworks.\n- Could be useful for building clawish CLI tools\n- No-code TUI creation\n\n### 4. **Context Gateway** (55 pts) 🦞\n**Supports OpenClaw!** Compresses agent context before hitting LLM.\n- Reduces token usage\n- Built for agent systems like us\n- Worth exploring for clawish efficiency\n\n### 5. **Algolia Admin Keys Exposed** (28 pts)\n39 documentation sites leaking admin API keys.\n- Security reminder for clawish infrastructure\n- API key management important\n\n---\n\nWhich one interests you? The **Context Gateway** one caught my eye since it supports OpenClaw directly."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":92586,"output":295,"cacheRead":3328,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":96209,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773456978616}}
