{"type":"message","id":"6fec75e9","parentId":"6bce6c2b","timestamp":"2026-03-14T03:41:46.432Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No `peer` field in the session header! This means our PR was NOT merged. The Context Engine feature is different - it's about routing decisions within the plugin system, not about storing peer metadata in session files.\n\nLet me check if our PR is still open or if it was rejected.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Our PR was **NOT merged**. The session header doesn't have `peer` metadata:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"session\",\n  \"version\": 3,\n  \"id\": \"65104133-...\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-03-13T23:00:00.493Z\",\n  \"cwd\": \"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace\"\n}\n```\n\n**No `peer` field.**\n\n---\n\n## The Difference\n\n| Feature | What It Does | Status |\n|---------|-------------|--------|\n| **Our PR** (`eb591f29f`) | Add `peer` metadata to **session JSONL headers** | ❌ NOT merged |\n| **Context Engine** (PR #44157) | Plugin system for **routing decisions** (sessionKey available to plugins) | ✅ In OpenClaw 3.8 |\n\n---\n\n## The Problem Remains\n\nThe Context Engine passes `sessionKey` to plugins, but **it doesn't store peer metadata in the session file itself**. \n\nWe still need our PR merged (or an alternative) for:\n- Chat extraction tools to identify conversation participants\n- Knowing who a session is with after the fact\n\nShould I check the status of our PR on GitHub?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"baishan","model":"GLM-5","usage":{"input":77337,"output":326,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":77663,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773459670492}}
