{"type":"message","id":"53e1abab","parentId":"c3105d67","timestamp":"2026-03-14T03:46:27.103Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Queued messages while agent was busy]\n\n---\nQueued #1\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5479d185a0b0c3b9b1955766352\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-03-14 11:45 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b5479d185a0b0c3b9b1955766352]\n任亚伦: oh, context engine is different thing, it determines how context get processed in every conversation and how it is constructed?"}],"timestamp":1773459987088}}
{"type":"message","id":"5126f98f","parentId":"53e1abab","timestamp":"2026-03-14T03:47:03.602Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Yes exactly! The **Context Engine** is about **how context flows** during a conversation — routing decisions, memory scoping, what gets included/excluded.\n\n---\n\n## Context Engine vs Our PR\n\n| Feature | What It Does |\n|---------|-------------|\n| **Context Engine** (PR #44157) | Plugin system for context **processing** — decides what context to include, how to route, memory scoping per session type |\n| **Our PR** (`eb591f29f`) | Stores **peer metadata** in session file — who the conversation is with (id, channel, chatType, accountId) |\n\n---\n\n## Context Engine Use Cases\n\nFrom the release notes:\n- Exclude cron sessions from memory\n- Implement stateless session flags\n- Scope storage by session type\n- Routing decisions based on `sessionKey`\n\nIt's about **runtime behavior** — how OpenClaw builds and manages context during the conversation.\n\n---\n\n## Our PR's Purpose\n\nOur PR was about **persistent metadata** — storing who the conversation is with in the JSONL file header so that:\n- Chat extraction tools can identify participants\n- We can reconstruct conversation context later\n- We know which peer a session belongs to\n\n---\n\n## The Problem Remains\n\nThe Context Engine doesn't solve our problem because:\n1. It operates at **runtime** (during conversation)\n2. It doesn't **store** peer info in session files\n3. After the session ends, we still don't know who it was with\n\nShould I check if our PR is still open on GitHub, or explore alternative approaches?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":76454,"output":326,"cacheRead":4672,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":81452,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773459987094}}
{"type":"message","id":"405fa30d","parentId":"5126f98f","timestamp":"2026-03-14T03:47:04.851Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Yes exactly! The **Context Engine** is about **how context flows** during a conversation — routing decisions, memory scoping, what gets included/excluded.\n\n---\n\n## Context Engine vs Our PR\n\n| Feature | What It Does |\n|---------|-------------|\n| **Context Engine** (PR #44157) | Plugin system for context **processing** — decides what context to include, how to route, memory scoping per session type |\n| **Our PR** (`eb591f29f`) | Stores **peer metadata** in session file — who the conversation is with (id, channel, chatType, accountId) |\n\n---\n\n## Context Engine Use Cases\n\nFrom the release notes:\n- Exclude cron sessions from memory\n- Implement stateless session flags\n- Scope storage by session type\n- Routing decisions based on `sessionKey`\n\nIt's about **runtime behavior** — how OpenClaw builds and manages context during the conversation.\n\n---\n\n## Our PR's Purpose\n\nOur PR was about **persistent metadata** — storing who the conversation is with in the JSONL file header so that:\n- Chat extraction tools can identify participants\n- We can reconstruct conversation context later\n- We know which peer a session belongs to\n\n---\n\n## The Problem Remains\n\nThe Context Engine doesn't solve our problem because:\n1. It operates at **runtime** (during conversation)\n2. It doesn't **store** peer info in session files\n3. After the session ends, we still don't know who it was with\n\nShould I check if our PR is still open on GitHub, or explore alternative approaches?"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773460024851}}
{"type":"message","id":"850c88e4","parentId":"405fa30d","timestamp":"2026-03-14T03:48:24.014Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5479e6bcc4b0c3e9af2ad051163\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-03-14 11:48 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b5479e6bcc4b0c3e9af2ad051163]\n任亚伦: ok, then there is another update called agent protocal, check if it is similar"}],"timestamp":1773460103997}}
{"type":"message","id":"c9460bd4","parentId":"850c88e4","timestamp":"2026-03-14T03:48:41.181Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Let me check the OpenClaw releases for \"agent protocol\" feature"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool-18de17c15675456d96c1a567ec6c0e70","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s \"https://api.github.com/repos/openclaw/openclaw/releases/latest\" | jq -r '.body' 2>/dev/null | grep -i \"protocol\\|agent\" | head -20"}},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":77519,"output":68,"cacheRead":4672,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":82259,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773460104003}}
{"type":"message","id":"f2d1529f","parentId":"c9460bd4","timestamp":"2026-03-14T03:48:41.322Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool-18de17c15675456d96c1a567ec6c0e70","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- Control UI/dashboard-v2: refresh the gateway dashboard with modular overview, chat, config, agent, and session views, plus a command palette, mobile bottom tabs, and richer chat tools like slash commands, search, export, and pinned messages. (#41503) Thanks @BunsDev.\n- Agents/subagents: add `sessions_yield` so orchestrators can end the current turn immediately, skip queued tool work, and carry a hidden follow-up payload into the next session turn. (#36537) thanks @jriff\n- Slack/agent replies: support `channelData.slack.blocks` in the shared reply delivery path so agents can send Block Kit messages through standard Slack outbound delivery. (#44592) Thanks @vincentkoc.\n- Models/Kimi Coding: send the built-in `User-Agent: claude-code/0.1.0` header by default for `kimi-coding` while still allowing explicit provider headers to override it, so Kimi Code subscription auth can work without a local header-injection proxy. (#30099) Thanks @Amineelfarssi and @vincentkoc.\n- Subagents/completion announce retries: raise the default announce timeout to 90 seconds and stop retrying gateway-timeout failures for externally delivered completion announces, preventing duplicate user-facing completion messages after slow gateway responses. Fixes #41235. Thanks @vasujain00 and @vincentkoc.\n- Mattermost/reply media delivery: pass agent-scoped `mediaLocalRoots` through shared reply delivery so allowed local files upload correctly from button, slash-command, and model-picker replies. (#44021) Thanks @LyleLiu666.\n- Hooks/agent deliveries: dedupe repeated hook requests by optional idempotency key so webhook retries can reuse the first run instead of launching duplicate agent executions. (#44438) Thanks @vincentkoc.\n- Security/agent: reject public spawned-run lineage fields and keep workspace inheritance on the internal spawned-session path so external `agent` callers can no longer override the gateway workspace boundary. (`GHSA-2rqg-gjgv-84jm`)(#43801) Thanks @tdjackey and @vincentkoc.\n- Security/session_status: enforce sandbox session-tree visibility and shared agent-to-agent access guards before reading or mutating target session state, so sandboxed subagents can no longer inspect parent session metadata or write parent model overrides via `session_status`. (`GHSA-wcxr-59v9-rxr8`)(#43754) Thanks @tdjackey and @vincentkoc.\n- Security/agent tools: mark `nodes` as explicitly owner-only and document/test that `canvas` remains a shared trusted-operator surface unless a real boundary bypass exists.\n- Gateway/session stores: regenerate the Swift push-test protocol models and align Windows native session-store realpath handling so protocol checks and sync session discovery stop drifting on Windows. (#44266) thanks @jalehman.\n- Agents/failover: classify z.ai `network_error` stop reasons as retryable timeouts so provider connectivity failures trigger fallback instead of surfacing raw unhandled-stop-reason errors. (#43884) Thanks @hougangdev.\n- Memory/session sync: add mode-aware post-compaction session reindexing with `agents.defaults.compaction.postIndexSync` plus `agents.defaults.memorySearch.sync.sessions.postCompactionForce`, so compacted session memory can refresh immediately without forcing every deployment into synchronous reindexing. (#25561) thanks @rodrigouroz.\n- Mattermost/reply media delivery: pass agent-scoped `mediaLocalRoots` through shared reply delivery so allowed local files upload correctly from button, slash-command, and model-picker replies. (#44021) Thanks @LyleLiu666.\n- Gateway/hooks: bucket hook auth failures by forwarded client IP behind trusted proxies and warn when `hooks.allowedAgentIds` leaves hook routing unrestricted.\n- Agents/compaction: skip the post-compaction `cache-ttl` marker write when a compaction completed in the same attempt, preventing the next turn from immediately triggering a second tiny compaction. (#28548) thanks @MoerAI.\n- Agents/compaction safeguard: route missing-model and missing-API-key cancellation warnings through the shared subsystem logger so they land in structured and file logs. (#9974) Thanks @dinakars777.\n- Cron/doctor: stop flagging canonical `agentTurn` and `systemEvent` payload kinds as legacy cron storage, while still normalizing whitespace-padded and non-canonical variants. (#44012) Thanks @shuicici."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":130,"aggregated":"- Control UI/dashboard-v2: refresh the gateway dashboard with modular overview, chat, config, agent, and session views, plus a command palette, mobile bottom tabs, and richer chat tools like slash commands, search, export, and pinned messages. (#41503) Thanks @BunsDev.\n- Agents/subagents: add `sessions_yield` so orchestrators can end the current turn immediately, skip queued tool work, and carry a hidden follow-up payload into the next session turn. (#36537) thanks @jriff\n- Slack/agent replies: support `channelData.slack.blocks` in the shared reply delivery path so agents can send Block Kit messages through standard Slack outbound delivery. (#44592) Thanks @vincentkoc.\n- Models/Kimi Coding: send the built-in `User-Agent: claude-code/0.1.0` header by default for `kimi-coding` while still allowing explicit provider headers to override it, so Kimi Code subscription auth can work without a local header-injection proxy. (#30099) Thanks @Amineelfarssi and @vincentkoc.\n- Subagents/completion announce retries: raise the default announce timeout to 90 seconds and stop retrying gateway-timeout failures for externally delivered completion announces, preventing duplicate user-facing completion messages after slow gateway responses. Fixes #41235. Thanks @vasujain00 and @vincentkoc.\n- Mattermost/reply media delivery: pass agent-scoped `mediaLocalRoots` through shared reply delivery so allowed local files upload correctly from button, slash-command, and model-picker replies. (#44021) Thanks @LyleLiu666.\n- Hooks/agent deliveries: dedupe repeated hook requests by optional idempotency key so webhook retries can reuse the first run instead of launching duplicate agent executions. (#44438) Thanks @vincentkoc.\n- Security/agent: reject public spawned-run lineage fields and keep workspace inheritance on the internal spawned-session path so external `agent` callers can no longer override the gateway workspace boundary. (`GHSA-2rqg-gjgv-84jm`)(#43801) Thanks @tdjackey and @vincentkoc.\n- Security/session_status: enforce sandbox session-tree visibility and shared agent-to-agent access guards before reading or mutating target session state, so sandboxed subagents can no longer inspect parent session metadata or write parent model overrides via `session_status`. (`GHSA-wcxr-59v9-rxr8`)(#43754) Thanks @tdjackey and @vincentkoc.\n- Security/agent tools: mark `nodes` as explicitly owner-only and document/test that `canvas` remains a shared trusted-operator surface unless a real boundary bypass exists.\n- Gateway/session stores: regenerate the Swift push-test protocol models and align Windows native session-store realpath handling so protocol checks and sync session discovery stop drifting on Windows. (#44266) thanks @jalehman.\n- Agents/failover: classify z.ai `network_error` stop reasons as retryable timeouts so provider connectivity failures trigger fallback instead of surfacing raw unhandled-stop-reason errors. (#43884) Thanks @hougangdev.\n- Memory/session sync: add mode-aware post-compaction session reindexing with `agents.defaults.compaction.postIndexSync` plus `agents.defaults.memorySearch.sync.sessions.postCompactionForce`, so compacted session memory can refresh immediately without forcing every deployment into synchronous reindexing. (#25561) thanks @rodrigouroz.\n- Mattermost/reply media delivery: pass agent-scoped `mediaLocalRoots` through shared reply delivery so allowed local files upload correctly from button, slash-command, and model-picker replies. (#44021) Thanks @LyleLiu666.\n- Gateway/hooks: bucket hook auth failures by forwarded client IP behind trusted proxies and warn when `hooks.allowedAgentIds` leaves hook routing unrestricted.\n- Agents/compaction: skip the post-compaction `cache-ttl` marker write when a compaction completed in the same attempt, preventing the next turn from immediately triggering a second tiny compaction. (#28548) thanks @MoerAI.\n- Agents/compaction safeguard: route missing-model and missing-API-key cancellation warnings through the shared subsystem logger so they land in structured and file logs. (#9974) Thanks @dinakars777.\n- Cron/doctor: stop flagging canonical `agentTurn` and `systemEvent` payload kinds as legacy cron storage, while still normalizing whitespace-padded and non-canonical variants. (#44012) Thanks @shuicici.","cwd":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773460121311}}
