{"type":"message","id":"b09a7f3c","parentId":"31b1e751","timestamp":"2026-03-14T03:56:01.727Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_bd9f6824dd27416ca1c9bdf9","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- OpenAI/GPT-5.4 fast mode: add configurable session-level fast toggles across `/fast`, TUI, Control UI, and ACP, with per-model config defaults and OpenAI/Codex request shaping.\n- Gateway/session discovery: discover disk-only and retired ACP session stores under custom templated `session.store` roots so ACP reconciliation, session-id/session-label targeting, and run-id fallback keep working after restart. (#44176) thanks @gumadeiras.\n- Gateway/session discovery: discover disk-only and retired ACP session stores under custom templated `session.store` roots so ACP reconciliation, session-id/session-label targeting, and run-id fallback keep working after restart. (#44176) thanks @gumadeiras.\n- ACP/client final-message delivery: preserve terminal assistant text snapshots before resolving `end_turn`, so ACP clients no longer drop the last visible reply when the gateway sends the final message body on the terminal chat event. (#17615) Thanks @pjeby."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":128,"aggregated":"- OpenAI/GPT-5.4 fast mode: add configurable session-level fast toggles across `/fast`, TUI, Control UI, and ACP, with per-model config defaults and OpenAI/Codex request shaping.\n- Gateway/session discovery: discover disk-only and retired ACP session stores under custom templated `session.store` roots so ACP reconciliation, session-id/session-label targeting, and run-id fallback keep working after restart. (#44176) thanks @gumadeiras.\n- Gateway/session discovery: discover disk-only and retired ACP session stores under custom templated `session.store` roots so ACP reconciliation, session-id/session-label targeting, and run-id fallback keep working after restart. (#44176) thanks @gumadeiras.\n- ACP/client final-message delivery: preserve terminal assistant text snapshots before resolving `end_turn`, so ACP clients no longer drop the last visible reply when the gateway sends the final message body on the terminal chat event. (#17615) Thanks @pjeby.","cwd":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773460561708}}
{"type":"message","id":"32fbdb1e","parentId":"b09a7f3c","timestamp":"2026-03-14T03:56:38.619Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on my research, here's what I found about **ACP (Agent Communication Protocol)**:\n\n---\n\n## ACP in OpenClaw\n\n**ACP** is a protocol for running external coding agents (like Codex, Claude Code, Gemini) through OpenClaw.\n\nFrom the release notes:\n- **Session discovery** — ACP session stores, session-id/session-label targeting, run-id fallback\n- **Client delivery** — preserves terminal assistant text snapshots\n- **Fast mode** — configurable session-level toggles across TUI, Control UI, and ACP\n\n---\n\n## How It Relates to Our PR\n\n| Feature | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| **ACP** | Protocol for running external agents (Codex, Claude Code) through OpenClaw |\n| **Context Engine** | Plugin system for context routing decisions |\n| **Our PR** | Store peer metadata in session JSONL files |\n\n**ACP is different from our PR.** ACP is about:\n- Running external coding agents\n- Session management for those agents\n- Communication protocol between OpenClaw and external tools\n\n---\n\n## Does ACP Solve Our Problem?\n\n**No.** ACP doesn't address storing peer metadata in session files. It's focused on:\n1. Running external agents (Codex, Claude Code, Gemini)\n2. Managing those agent sessions\n3. Protocol for communication\n\nOur PR was about **identifying who a conversation is with** in the session file itself — which is still not solved.\n\nShould I check if there's a way to submit our PR again or find an alternative approach?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":50827,"output":324,"cacheRead":2816,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":53967,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773460561722}}
