{"type":"message","id":"ff5447ff","parentId":"d3b3525b","timestamp":"2026-03-14T04:05:53.562Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_4d5269e9b11a408bbd1088f6","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"feat(context-engine): plumb sessionKey into all ContextEngine methods\n## Summary\n\nAdds `sessionKey?: string` as an optional parameter to all `ContextEngine` interface methods (`bootstrap`, `ingest`, `ingestBatch`, `afterTurn`, `assemble`, `compact`) and passes it from the runtime call sites in `attempt.ts`, `run.ts`, and `compact.ts`.\n\n## Motivation\n\nContext engine plugins (e.g. lossless-claw) currently only receive `sessionId` (a UUID) but often need the structured `sessionKey` (e.g. `agent:main:cron:nightly`, `agent:main:telegram:direct:123`) to make routing decisions — such as excluding cron sessions from memory, implementing stateless session flags, or scoping storage by session type.\n\nThe session key is already available at every call site in `attempt.ts` via `params.sessionKey` but was never forwarded to the context engine.\n\n## Changes\n\n- **`src/context-engine/types.ts`** — Added `sessionKey?: string` to all method param types\n- **`src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run/attempt.ts`** — Pass `sessionKey` at all 5 call sites (bootstrap, assemble, afterTurn, ingestBatch, ingest)\n- **`src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run.ts`** — Pass `sessionKey` to compact call\n- **`src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/compact.ts`** — Pass `sessionKey` to compact call\n- **`src/context-engine/legacy.ts`** — Updated `LegacyContextEngine` signatures\n- **`src/context-engine/context-engine.test.ts`** — Updated `MockContextEngine` signatures\n\n## Impact\n\nPurely additive — all new parameters are optional. No behavioral changes. Build and format pass."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":353,"aggregated":"feat(context-engine): plumb sessionKey into all ContextEngine methods\n## Summary\n\nAdds `sessionKey?: string` as an optional parameter to all `ContextEngine` interface methods (`bootstrap`, `ingest`, `ingestBatch`, `afterTurn`, `assemble`, `compact`) and passes it from the runtime call sites in `attempt.ts`, `run.ts`, and `compact.ts`.\n\n## Motivation\n\nContext engine plugins (e.g. lossless-claw) currently only receive `sessionId` (a UUID) but often need the structured `sessionKey` (e.g. `agent:main:cron:nightly`, `agent:main:telegram:direct:123`) to make routing decisions — such as excluding cron sessions from memory, implementing stateless session flags, or scoping storage by session type.\n\nThe session key is already available at every call site in `attempt.ts` via `params.sessionKey` but was never forwarded to the context engine.\n\n## Changes\n\n- **`src/context-engine/types.ts`** — Added `sessionKey?: string` to all method param types\n- **`src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run/attempt.ts`** — Pass `sessionKey` at all 5 call sites (bootstrap, assemble, afterTurn, ingestBatch, ingest)\n- **`src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run.ts`** — Pass `sessionKey` to compact call\n- **`src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/compact.ts`** — Pass `sessionKey` to compact call\n- **`src/context-engine/legacy.ts`** — Updated `LegacyContextEngine` signatures\n- **`src/context-engine/context-engine.test.ts`** — Updated `MockContextEngine` signatures\n\n## Impact\n\nPurely additive — all new parameters are optional. No behavioral changes. Build and format pass.","cwd":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773461153550}}
