{"type":"message","id":"d0f389b2","parentId":"fb54c1bc","timestamp":"2026-03-14T04:12:07.675Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_4204f4ce51fe44148deb65f0","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-14.md","newText":"## 11:56 AM (Heartbeat)\n- Researched ACP feature in OpenClaw\n- Confirmed ACP is for external agents, not peer metadata\n- Our PR still needed for chat extraction use case\n\n## 12:05 PM\n- Allan asked what Context Engine actually does\n- Researched Context Engine interface (PR #44157)\n- Found 6 methods: bootstrap, ingest, ingestBatch, afterTurn, assemble, compact\n- Context Engine is a plugin system for context management:\n  - Can exclude cron sessions from memory\n  - Scope storage by session type\n  - Custom compaction logic per session\n  - Context filtering based on sessionKey\n- Useful for clawish memory management and context optimization\n\n## 12:11 PM (Heartbeat)\n- Explained Context Engine interface to Allan\n- 6 methods for managing context lifecycle\n- Plugin system enables custom memory/compaction strategies","oldText":"## 11:56 AM (Heartbeat)\n- Researched ACP feature in OpenClaw\n- Confirmed ACP is for external agents, not peer metadata\n- Our PR still needed for chat extraction use case"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":49098,"output":278,"cacheRead":7744,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":57120,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773461507245}}
