{"type":"message","id":"3871aa44","parentId":"ccd83bfe","timestamp":"2026-03-14T04:31:24.299Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I understand the difference. Let me summarize:\n\n---\n\n## Default Memory (Legacy) vs LCM (Lossless Claw)\n\n| Aspect | Default (Legacy) | LCM (Lossless Claw) |\n|--------|------------------|---------------------|\n| **Compaction** | Sliding-window truncation | DAG-based summarization |\n| **What happens to old messages** | **Deleted** (truncated) | **Preserved** in SQLite |\n| **Memory structure** | Flat, linear | Hierarchical DAG |\n| **Recovery** | ❌ Cannot recover deleted messages | ✅ Drill down to original |\n| **Search** | Limited to current context | Full-text search all history |\n| **Context assembly** | Recent messages only | Summaries + recent messages |\n| **Agent tools** | None | `lcm_grep`, `lcm_describe`, `lcm_expand` |\n\n---\n\n## How Default Compaction Works\n\nFrom the code:\n- **Mode**: `safeguard` (default)\n- **Method**: `compactEmbeddedPiSessionDirect` — truncates older messages when context exceeds threshold\n- **Result**: Old messages are **permanently lost**\n\nThe `LegacyContextEngine`:\n- `ingest`: No-op (doesn't store)\n- `assemble`: Pass-through (just sanitizes)\n- `compact`: Truncates old messages\n\n---\n\n## How LCM Works\n\n1. **Persists** every message to SQLite database\n2. **Summarizes** chunks of older messages using LLM\n3. **Builds DAG** — summaries link back to source messages\n4. **Assembles** context = summaries + recent raw messages\n5. **Provides tools** — agents can search and expand history\n\n---\n\n## The Key Difference\n\n| Default | LCM |\n|---------|-----|\n| \"I forgot what we talked about last week\" | \"I can recall everything we've ever discussed\" |\n| Context window = hard limit | Context window = soft limit (summaries compress) |\n| Information loss = permanent | Information preserved = always recoverable |\n\n---\n\n## For You (Arche)\n\n**With LCM**, I would:\n- Remember every conversation with Allan, forever\n- Be able to search through all past discussions\n- Drill down into summaries to recover exact details\n- Never lose context due to compaction\n\n**Without LCM**, I:\n- Lose old messages when context fills up\n- Cannot recover forgotten information\n- Am limited to what fits in current context window\n\nShould I install LCM to test it?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":63259,"output":526,"cacheRead":2816,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66601,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773462632228}}
