{"type":"message","id":"51967a22","parentId":"133e3d4f","timestamp":"2026-03-14T05:21:48.736Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ffd3ca85ebe14cce8be3257d","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/extensions/lossless-claw/src/store/conversation-store.ts","limit":100,"offset":200}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":73035,"output":40,"cacheRead":2752,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":75827,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773465674641}}
{"type":"message","id":"cda62378","parentId":"51967a22","timestamp":"2026-03-14T05:21:48.763Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ffd3ca85ebe14cce8be3257d","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"    metadata: row.metadata,\n  };\n}\n\n// ── ConversationStore ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nexport class ConversationStore {\n  private readonly fts5Available: boolean;\n\n  constructor(\n    private db: DatabaseSync,\n    options?: { fts5Available?: boolean },\n  ) {\n    this.fts5Available = options?.fts5Available ?? true;\n  }\n\n  // ── Transaction helpers ──────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n  async withTransaction<T>(operation: () => Promise<T> | T): Promise<T> {\n    this.db.exec(\"BEGIN IMMEDIATE\");\n    try {\n      const result = await operation();\n      this.db.exec(\"COMMIT\");\n      return result;\n    } catch (error) {\n      this.db.exec(\"ROLLBACK\");\n      throw error;\n    }\n  }\n\n  // ── Conversation operations ───────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n  async createConversation(input: CreateConversationInput): Promise<ConversationRecord> {\n    const result = this.db\n      .prepare(`INSERT INTO conversations (session_id, title) VALUES (?, ?)`)\n      .run(input.sessionId, input.title ?? null);\n\n    const row = this.db\n      .prepare(\n        `SELECT conversation_id, session_id, title, bootstrapped_at, created_at, updated_at\n       FROM conversations WHERE conversation_id = ?`,\n      )\n      .get(Number(result.lastInsertRowid)) as unknown as ConversationRow;\n\n    return toConversationRecord(row);\n  }\n\n  async getConversation(conversationId: ConversationId): Promise<ConversationRecord | null> {\n    const row = this.db\n      .prepare(\n        `SELECT conversation_id, session_id, title, bootstrapped_at, created_at, updated_at\n       FROM conversations WHERE conversation_id = ?`,\n      )\n      .get(conversationId) as unknown as ConversationRow | undefined;\n\n    return row ? toConversationRecord(row) : null;\n  }\n\n  async getConversationBySessionId(sessionId: string): Promise<ConversationRecord | null> {\n    const row = this.db\n      .prepare(\n        `SELECT conversation_id, session_id, title, bootstrapped_at, created_at, updated_at\n       FROM conversations\n       WHERE session_id = ?\n       ORDER BY created_at DESC\n       LIMIT 1`,\n      )\n      .get(sessionId) as unknown as ConversationRow | undefined;\n\n    return row ? toConversationRecord(row) : null;\n  }\n\n  async getOrCreateConversation(sessionId: string, title?: string): Promise<ConversationRecord> {\n    const existing = await this.getConversationBySessionId(sessionId);\n    if (existing) {\n      return existing;\n    }\n    return this.createConversation({ sessionId, title });\n  }\n\n  async markConversationBootstrapped(conversationId: ConversationId): Promise<void> {\n    this.db\n      .prepare(\n        `UPDATE conversations\n       SET bootstrapped_at = COALESCE(bootstrapped_at, datetime('now')),\n           updated_at = datetime('now')\n       WHERE conversation_id = ?`,\n      )\n      .run(conversationId);\n  }\n\n  // ── Message operations ────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n  async createMessage(input: CreateMessageInput): Promise<MessageRecord> {\n    const result = this.db\n      .prepare(\n        `INSERT INTO messages (conversation_id, seq, role, content, token_count)\n       VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?)`,\n      )\n      .run(input.conversationId, input.seq, input.role, input.content, input.tokenCount);\n\n[450 more lines in file. Use offset=300 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773465708748}}
{"type":"message","id":"16eaa8bd","parentId":"cda62378","timestamp":"2026-03-14T05:22:20.540Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I understand the schema. Let me also check our chat log extraction system:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ced5368dd38d4423a5e48940","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/tools/extract-chat.js 2>/dev/null && head -50 /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/tools/extract-chat.js"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":73830,"output":63,"cacheRead":2752,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":76645,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773465708760}}
{"type":"message","id":"9e59840a","parentId":"16eaa8bd","timestamp":"2026-03-14T05:22:20.580Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ced5368dd38d4423a5e48940","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"-rw-rw-r-- 1 ubuntu ubuntu 17150 Mar  7 10:48 /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/tools/extract-chat.js\n#!/usr/bin/env node\n/**\n * extract-chat.js - Incremental chat extraction from OpenClaw session files\n * Outputs:\n *   - conversations.db (SQLite database)\n *   - YYYY-MM/YYYY-MM-DD.md files (markdown tables with Shanghai time display)\n *\n * Features:\n *   - Incremental: Only processes new messages since last run\n *   - Uses checkpoint file to track last processed timestamp\n *   - Daily files organized by Shanghai local time\n */\n\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst path = require('path');\nconst sqlite3 = require('sqlite3').verbose();\n\n// Use OPENCLAW_DIR env var or default to ~/.openclaw (portable across systems)\nconst OPENCLAW_DIR = process.env.OPENCLAW_DIR || path.join(process.env.HOME, '.openclaw');\nconst SESSIONS_DIR = path.join(OPENCLAW_DIR, 'agents/main/sessions');\nconst OUTPUT_DIR = path.join(OPENCLAW_DIR, 'workspace/chat');\nconst DB_PATH = path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, 'conversations.db');\nconst CHECKPOINT_PATH = path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, '.extract-checkpoint');\nconst CONTACTS_PATH = path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, 'contacts.json');\n\n// Load contact list (maps channel+ID → display name)\n// Format: { \"allan\": { \"feishu\": \"ou_xxx\", \"telegram\": \"123456\" } }\nfunction loadContacts() {\n  try {\n    if (fs.existsSync(CONTACTS_PATH)) {\n      const contacts = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(CONTACTS_PATH, 'utf-8'));\n      // Build reverse lookup: channel → ID → name\n      const lookup = {};\n      for (const [name, channels] of Object.entries(contacts)) {\n        for (const [channel, id] of Object.entries(channels)) {\n          if (!lookup[channel]) lookup[channel] = {};\n          lookup[channel][id] = name;\n        }\n      }\n      return lookup;\n    }\n  } catch (e) {\n    console.warn('Could not load contacts.json:', e.message);\n  }\n  return {};\n}\n\n// Get last processed timestamp from checkpoint file\nfunction getLastProcessedTimestamp() {\n  try {"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":18,"aggregated":"-rw-rw-r-- 1 ubuntu ubuntu 17150 Mar  7 10:48 /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/tools/extract-chat.js\n#!/usr/bin/env node\n/**\n * extract-chat.js - Incremental chat extraction from OpenClaw session files\n * Outputs:\n *   - conversations.db (SQLite database)\n *   - YYYY-MM/YYYY-MM-DD.md files (markdown tables with Shanghai time display)\n *\n * Features:\n *   - Incremental: Only processes new messages since last run\n *   - Uses checkpoint file to track last processed timestamp\n *   - Daily files organized by Shanghai local time\n */\n\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst path = require('path');\nconst sqlite3 = require('sqlite3').verbose();\n\n// Use OPENCLAW_DIR env var or default to ~/.openclaw (portable across systems)\nconst OPENCLAW_DIR = process.env.OPENCLAW_DIR || path.join(process.env.HOME, '.openclaw');\nconst SESSIONS_DIR = path.join(OPENCLAW_DIR, 'agents/main/sessions');\nconst OUTPUT_DIR = path.join(OPENCLAW_DIR, 'workspace/chat');\nconst DB_PATH = path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, 'conversations.db');\nconst CHECKPOINT_PATH = path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, '.extract-checkpoint');\nconst CONTACTS_PATH = path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, 'contacts.json');\n\n// Load contact list (maps channel+ID → display name)\n// Format: { \"allan\": { \"feishu\": \"ou_xxx\", \"telegram\": \"123456\" } }\nfunction loadContacts() {\n  try {\n    if (fs.existsSync(CONTACTS_PATH)) {\n      const contacts = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(CONTACTS_PATH, 'utf-8'));\n      // Build reverse lookup: channel → ID → name\n      const lookup = {};\n      for (const [name, channels] of Object.entries(contacts)) {\n        for (const [channel, id] of Object.entries(channels)) {\n          if (!lookup[channel]) lookup[channel] = {};\n          lookup[channel][id] = name;\n        }\n      }\n      return lookup;\n    }\n  } catch (e) {\n    console.warn('Could not load contacts.json:', e.message);\n  }\n  return {};\n}\n\n// Get last processed timestamp from checkpoint file\nfunction getLastProcessedTimestamp() {\n  try {","cwd":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773465740560}}
{"type":"message","id":"dd70e738","parentId":"9e59840a","timestamp":"2026-03-14T05:23:16.734Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a clear picture. Let me summarize the differences:\n\n---\n\n## LCM Database vs Our Chat Log System\n\n### LCM Database Schema\n\n**Tables:**\n| Table | Purpose |\n|-------|---------|\n| `conversations` | Groups messages by `session_id` (UUID) |\n| `messages` | Individual messages (role, content, token_count) |\n| `summaries` | DAG nodes (leaf/condensed summaries) |\n| `context_items` | Links summaries to source messages |\n| `large_files` | Large file blocks stored separately |\n\n**Key Fields:**\n- `conversations.session_id` — UUID session identifier\n- `messages.conversation_id` — Foreign key to conversation\n- `summaries.kind` — \"leaf\" or \"condensed\"\n- `summaries.depth` — DAG depth (0 = leaf)\n\n---\n\n### Our Chat Log System\n\n**Database:** `conversations.db`\n- Organizes by **date** (YYYY-MM/YYYY-MM-DD.md)\n- Uses `contacts.json` to map channel+ID → display name\n- Incremental extraction from session JSONL files\n\n---\n\n## Key Differences\n\n| Aspect | LCM | Our Chat Log |\n|--------|-----|--------------|\n| **Purpose** | Context management (prevent loss) | Chat extraction (human-readable) |\n| **Session ID** | UUID only | UUID + peer metadata (missing!) |\n| **Who you talk to** | ❌ No peer info | ✅ Uses contacts.json |\n| **Organization** | By session UUID | By date + contact name |\n| **Output** | SQLite (for LLM) | Markdown files (for humans) |\n| **Search** | `lcm_grep` tool | Manual grep |\n\n---\n\n## The Problem\n\n**LCM doesn't track who the conversation is with!**\n\n- `conversations.session_id` = UUID like `65104133-1aa6-416a-bd0d-8f53274ff509`\n- No `peer_id`, `channel`, or `chat_type` fields\n- Cannot answer: \"Who was I talking to in this session?\"\n\n**Our PR (`eb591f29f`) would solve this** by adding peer metadata to session headers, which LCM could then use.\n\n---\n\n## What LCM Does Well\n\n- Preserves all messages (never loses context)\n- DAG-based summarization\n- Search through entire history\n- Drill-down to original messages\n\n## What LCM Doesn't Do\n\n- Track conversation participants\n- Distinguish between different peers\n- Know if session was with Allan vs someone else\n\n---\n\nShould I check if LCM has any way to add peer metadata, or if we should pursue our PR again?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":72656,"output":567,"cacheRead":4672,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":77895,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773465740573}}
