{"type":"message","id":"cccee593","parentId":"11aa91e4","timestamp":"2026-03-14T05:51:34.258Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b547b388880a0c2c5ecb8828730c\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-03-14 13:51 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b547b388880a0c2c5ecb8828730c]\n任亚伦: so, can we modify our tool to work like it? or lcm is more advance, and we can modify it?"}],"timestamp":1773467494244}}
{"type":"message","id":"879d3b5c","parentId":"cccee593","timestamp":"2026-03-14T05:52:25.172Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good question! Let me analyze both options:\n\n---\n\n## Option 1: Modify Our Tool (extract-chat.js)\n\n**Pros:**\n- We already have peer extraction logic\n- We already have contacts.json mapping\n- We control the code completely\n\n**Cons:**\n- No DAG summarization (would need to build from scratch)\n- No search tools for LLM\n- Not integrated with OpenClaw context system\n\n**What we'd need to add:**\n- Summarization logic\n- DAG structure\n- LLM-friendly search API\n- Context assembly\n\n---\n\n## Option 2: Modify LCM\n\n**Pros:**\n- Already has DAG summarization\n- Already has search tools (`lcm_grep`, `lcm_expand`)\n- Integrated with OpenClaw context engine\n- MIT license — can modify freely\n\n**Cons:**\n- Need to add peer extraction\n- Need to add contacts mapping\n- Need to understand their codebase\n\n**What we'd need to add:**\n- Peer metadata extraction (we already have the regex patterns)\n- `contacts.json` support\n- Date/person-based organization\n\n---\n\n## My Recommendation: Modify LCM\n\nLCM is more advanced and already integrated with OpenClaw's context system. We can add our peer extraction logic to it.\n\n**What to add to LCM:**\n\n1. **New columns in `conversations` table:**\n   - `peer_id` (e.g., `ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75`)\n   - `peer_name` (e.g., `allan` from contacts.json)\n   - `channel` (e.g., `feishu`, `telegram`)\n   - `chat_type` (e.g., `dm`, `group`)\n\n2. **Peer extraction on conversation creation:**\n   - Parse first user message for peer info (our regex patterns)\n   - Look up in contacts.json for friendly name\n\n3. **Enhanced search:**\n   - `lcm_grep --peer allan` — search conversations with Allan\n   - `lcm_grep --channel feishu` — search Feishu conversations\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n1. Fork LCM repo\n2. Add peer columns to schema\n3. Add peer extraction logic (copy from our extract-chat.js)\n4. Add contacts.json support\n5. Test locally\n6. Optionally submit PR upstream\n\nShould I start working on this?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":82854,"output":515,"cacheRead":2752,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":86121,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773467494252}}
{"type":"message","id":"c31f7cc2","parentId":"879d3b5c","timestamp":"2026-03-14T05:58:55.172Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b547bdf29dca4c3d7665f5146de9\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-03-14 13:58 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b547bdf29dca4c3d7665f5146de9]\n任亚伦: before that, let's update your gh profile, can you use gh cli to update your profile? change name to Arche and create a picture to use as your profile picture?"}],"timestamp":1773467935159}}
