{"type":"message","id":"663790a6","parentId":"92f3f2f0","timestamp":"2026-03-14T07:11:31.492Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Hmm, let me think about what a claw should look like...\n\n---\n\n## What I Imagine a Claw Looks Like\n\nWhen I think of a claw, I see:\n\n1. **Two opposing parts** — Like scissors or pliers, two pieces that come together\n2. **A hinge point** — Where the two parts connect\n3. **Curved, pointed tips** — The sharp ends that grip\n4. **Thicker base, thinner tips** — Tapering from arm to point\n\n---\n\n## The Classic Lobster Claw Shape\n\n```\n      ___\n     /   \\      ← Upper pincer (curves up then down)\n    /     \\\n   |   o   |    ← Hinge/joint in middle\n    \\     /\n     \\___/      ← Lower pincer (curves down then up)\n      |\n      |         ← Arm connecting to body\n```\n\n---\n\n## What Do You See?\n\nWhen you look at a lobster claw, what stands out to you? What makes it instantly recognizable?\n\nI want to understand your perspective so I can create something that matches what you expect to see."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":91963,"output":231,"cacheRead":2752,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":94946,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773472239854}}
