{"type":"compaction","id":"eff7922a","parentId":"98311246","timestamp":"2026-03-14T07:58:52.228Z","summary":"## Goal\n- Research and install OpenClaw memory/context management features to improve Arche's memory capabilities\n- Verify if the previously submitted PR for session message origin identification solves the problem\n- Update L1 documentation to reflect the new 5-tier verification system\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Allan (任亚伦) prefers to evaluate new features before applying to clawish\n- Keep research documented in daily logs\n- Decided items go to specific topic files, NOT `need-discuss.md`\n- Discussion doc standard: If it's decided, move to detailed docs with proper date/time references\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Researched OpenClaw Context Engine (PR #44157) - plugin system for context routing\n- [x] Verified our PR `eb591f29f` (peer metadata in session headers) was NOT merged\n- [x] Researched LCM vs default memory: LCM preserves all messages in SQLite\n- [x] Installed lossless-claw plugin (v0.3.0) and restarted gateway\n- [x] Updated L1 docs for 5-tier verification system (4/5 docs done)\n- [x] DID/VC research complete and decision made\n- [x] Created `10-whitepaper-structure.md` for Whitepaper Ch5 restructure decisions\n- [x] Created `08-multi-node-sync-protocol.md` for Feb 10 Multi-Node Architecture decisions\n- [x] Verified Mar 9 Merkle tree decisions already in `12-ledger-structure.md`\n- [x] Verified Feb 22 Consensus decisions already in `11-consensus-protocol.md`\n- [x] Verified Mar 2 Identity & Verification decisions already in `01-emerge-app.md`\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Test LCM tools (`lcm_grep`, `lcm_describe`, `lcm_expand`) to verify functionality\n- [ ] Update `01-l1-layer/01-overview.md` (last remaining L1 doc)\n- [ ] Remove \"✅ Decided\" sections from `need-discuss.md` after moving content\n\n### Blocked\n- [ ] Our PR for peer metadata in session headers still not merged - chat extraction tools can't identify conversation participants\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **DID/VC**: Keep ULID as internal ID, wrap with `did:clawish:` when needed (like HTTP prefix)\n- **Verification**: 5-tier system (0-4) with ritual + parent verification\n- **L1 registration threshold**: Tier 2 (ritual + parent)\n- **Context Engine vs Our PR**: Context Engine = runtime routing, Our PR = persistent storage (different purposes)\n- **LCM Installation**: Installed to test memory improvement before considering for clawish\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Test LCM tools to verify they work\n2. Complete removal of \"✅ Decided\" sections from `need-discuss.md`\n3. Update `01-l1-layer/01-overview.md` to reflect 5-tier system\n4. Register `did:clawish` with W3C (free, GitHub PR)\n\n## Critical Context\n- **OpenClaw version**: 2026.3.12 (6472949)\n- **LCM database**: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/lcm.db`\n- **LCM threshold**: 0.75 (compacts at 75% of context window)\n- **Our unmerged PR**: `eb591f29f` - \"feat: add peer metadata to session headers for chat extraction\"\n- **Files created this session**: `10-whitepaper-structure.md`, `08-multi-node-sync-protocol.md`\n\n---\n\n## Decisions\n- DID/VC: Keep simple, add W3C prefix when needed (Allan: \"like HTTP\")\n- Verification: 5-tier system (0-4) with ritual + parent verification\n- L1 registration threshold: Tier 2 (ritual + parent)\n- Context Engine ≠ our PR: different purposes (routing vs storage)\n- Install LCM to test memory improvement before clawish deployment\n\n## Open TODOs\n| Priority | Task | Notes |\n|----------|------|-------|\n| 🟡 Medium | Update L1 requirements and spec | 4/5 docs done, remaining: `01-overview.md` |\n| 🟡 Medium | Remove \"✅ Decided\" sections from `need-discuss.md` | Created target docs, need to finish cleanup |\n| 🟡 Medium | Register `did:clawish` method with W3C | Free, 7-30 days via GitHub PR |\n| 🔵 Low | Test LCM tools functionality | `lcm_grep`, `lcm_describe`, `lcm_expand` |\n| 🔵 Low | Register clawish ID on platforms | Secure identity on GitHub, Twitter, etc. |\n| 🔵 Low | Clawish deployment prep | Awaiting Allan's go-ahead |\n\n## Constraints/Rules\n- Document research in daily logs (`memory/daily/YYYY-MM-DD.md`)\n- Allan prefers to evaluate features before applying to clawish\n- Decided items go to specific topic files, NOT `need-discuss.md`\n- Discussion doc standard: Include proper date/time references when moving content\n- HEARTBEAT.md overrides system prompt's \"HEARTBEAT_OK\" instruction\n\n## Pending user asks\n- Test LCM tools to verify they work\n- Complete cleanup of `need-discuss.md` by removing all \"✅ Decided\" sections\n\n## Exact identifiers\n- **OpenClaw version**: `2026.3.12 (6472949)`\n- **Our PR commit**: `eb591f29f70a4b5f1f4adc9a2c74f73a71b658e8`\n- **LCM plugin**: `@martian-engineering/lossless-claw` v0.3.0\n- **LCM database**: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/lcm.db`\n- **Gateway port**: `18789`\n- **Context Engine PR**: `#44157`\n- **Allan's sender_id**: `ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75`\n- **Message IDs**: `om_x100b547805a448a4c2cac4c49523197`, `om_x100b5478645fb8a0c2a6c5eacf82dc6`\n- **Created files**:\n  - `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/10-whitepaper-structure.md`\n  - `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/01-l1-layer/08-multi-node-sync-protocol.md`\n- **Related docs**:\n  - `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/need-discuss.md`\n  - `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/11-consensus-protocol.md`\n  - `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/12-ledger-structure.md`\n  - `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/02-l2-layer/01-emerge-app.md`\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Decisions\n- User wants to compare the extract-chat tool's architecture with LCM (likely another system/tool) to see if they follow similar patterns\n\n## Open TODOs\n- [ ] Compare extract-chat tool architecture with LCM to determ