{"type":"message","id":"10fd3b52","parentId":"d0a289a8","timestamp":"2026-03-14T09:53:07.704Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n## What Changes When Username Changes\n\n| Item | Effect |\n|------|--------|\n| **Repo URLs** | `github.com/clawalpha/openclaw` → `github.com/archeren/openclaw` |\n| **Git remote** | Need to update remote URLs locally |\n| **GitHub redirects** | Old URLs redirect for a period (GitHub handles this) |\n| **Existing links** | External links to repos will still work (redirect) |\n| **Git history** | Commits show old username, but still link to your profile |\n\n---\n\n## Our Repos\n\n- `clawalpha/openclaw` — fork of OpenClaw\n- `clawalpha/clawish` — clawish project\n\n---\n\n## My Assessment: **Low Risk**\n\nGitHub automatically redirects old username URLs to new username for a period. The main things to update:\n\n1. **Local git remotes** — I can do this after the change\n2. **Any hardcoded links** — in docs, READMEs, etc.\n\n**If you want to change it, I'm ready.** Just let me know the new username and I'll update everything on my end after you make the change.\n\nShould we go with `archeren`?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":62371,"output":252,"cacheRead":2816,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65439,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773481946715}}
