{"type":"message","id":"0d7c7102","parentId":"052798c1","timestamp":"2026-03-14T12:51:39.021Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me summarize the LCM improvement plan:\n\n---\n\n## LCM Improvement Plan\n\nBased on our earlier analysis, here's what we can improve:\n\n### Current LCM Gaps\n\n| Gap | Description |\n|-----|-------------|\n| **No peer metadata** | Can't search by \"who I talked to\" |\n| **No contacts mapping** | IDs like `ou_xxx` aren't resolved to names |\n| **Session-only organization** | No date/person-based grouping |\n\n### What We Can Add\n\n| Feature | Description | Priority |\n|---------|-------------|----------|\n| **Peer columns** | Add `peer_id`, `peer_name`, `channel`, `chat_type` to `conversations` table | 🔴 High |\n| **Peer extraction** | Parse message content for peer info (our regex patterns) | 🔴 High |\n| **contacts.json support** | Map IDs to friendly names | 🟡 Medium |\n| **Enhanced search** | `lcm_grep --peer allan`, `lcm_grep --channel feishu` | 🟡 Medium |\n| **Date organization** | Group conversations by date | 🟢 Low |\n\n### Implementation Approach\n\n**Option A: Fork LCM**\n- Clone `Martian-Engineering/lossless-claw`\n- Add peer columns to schema\n- Add peer extraction logic\n- Submit PR upstream\n\n**Option B: Create Plugin Extension**\n- Create a new plugin that extends LCM\n- Add peer tracking layer on top\n- Less invasive, easier to maintain\n\n---\n\n## Questions for You\n\n1. **Fork or extend?** Do you prefer forking LCM directly or creating a separate plugin?\n2. **Priority?** Should we focus on peer tracking first, or other features?\n3. **Upstream contribution?** Do you want to contribute changes back to LCM?\n\nWhat do you think?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":70006,"output":389,"cacheRead":9472,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":79867,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773492646114}}
{"type":"message","id":"40e0108c","parentId":"0d7c7102","timestamp":"2026-03-14T12:55:18.789Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5461e5828538c38b41acb9fc054\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-03-14 20:55 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b5461e5828538c38b41acb9fc054]\n任亚伦: what about add a table for contacts?"}],"timestamp":1773492918772}}
{"type":"message","id":"ef67db5e","parentId":"40e0108c","timestamp":"2026-03-14T12:56:05.143Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good idea! A separate `contacts` table is cleaner than adding columns to `conversations`. Let me design it:\n\n---\n\n## LCM Schema Enhancement: Contacts Table\n\n### New Table: `contacts`\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE contacts (\n  peer_id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,        -- e.g., 'ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75'\n  peer_name TEXT,                   -- e.g., 'Allan', '任亚伦'\n  channel TEXT,                     -- e.g., 'feishu', 'telegram', 'discord'\n  display_name TEXT,                -- Friendly name for UI\n  avatar_url TEXT,                  -- Optional avatar\n  metadata JSON,                    -- Additional info (platform-specific)\n  first_seen_at TEXT,               -- When we first talked\n  last_seen_at TEXT,                -- Last conversation\n  conversation_count INTEGER,       -- How many conversations\n  created_at TEXT,\n  updated_at TEXT\n);\n```\n\n### Modified `conversations` Table\n\n```sql\nALTER TABLE conversations ADD COLUMN peer_id TEXT;\nALTER TABLE conversations ADD COLUMN channel TEXT;\nALTER TABLE conversations ADD COLUMN chat_type TEXT;  -- 'dm' or 'group'\n```\n\n### How It Works\n\n1. **On new conversation:**\n   - Extract peer info from first message (our regex patterns)\n   - Look up in `contacts` table\n   - If new contact → create entry\n   - Link conversation to contact via `peer_id`\n\n2. **Search capabilities:**\n   - `lcm_grep --peer allan` → finds all conversations with Allan\n   - `lcm_grep --channel feishu` → all Feishu conversations\n   - `lcm_grep --chat-type dm` → all DMs\n\n3. **Contacts sync:**\n   - Can import from `contacts.json` (our existing file)\n   - Auto-populate from message parsing\n\n---\n\n## Benefits\n\n| Benefit | Description |\n|---------|-------------|\n| **Clean separation** | Contacts are separate from conversations |\n| **Reusable** | Same contact across multiple conversations |\n| **Queryable** | \"Who have I talked to?\" queries |\n| **Syncable** | Can import/export contacts |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Steps\n\n1. Fork LCM repo\n2. Add `contacts` table to schema\n3. Add `peer_id`, `channel`, `chat_type` to `conversations`\n4. Add peer extraction logic (from our `extract-chat.js`)\n5. Add `contacts.json` import\n6. Update search tools to support peer filtering\n\nWant me to start working on this?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":78301,"output":548,"cacheRead":1600,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":80449,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773492918778}}
{"type":"message","id":"9f2ad2c7","parentId":"ef67db5e","timestamp":"2026-03-14T12:57:35.585Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5461fd26c93cc2dd0115f3a70bf\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-03-14 20:57 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b5461fd26c93cc2dd0115f3a70bf]\n任亚伦: the contact table can be simplified"}],"timestamp":1773493055573}}
{"type":"message","id":"b2652d17","parentId":"9f2ad2c7","timestamp":"2026-03-14T12:58:12.285Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You're right. Let me simplify:\n\n---\n\n## Simplified Contacts Table\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE contacts (\n  peer_id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,        -- e.g., 'ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75'\n  peer_name TEXT,                   -- e.g., 'Allan', '任亚伦'\n  channel TEXT                      -- e.g., 'feishu', 'telegram'\n);\n```\n\nJust the essentials:\n- **Who** — `peer_id` + `peer_name`\n- **Where** — `channel`\n\nEverything else (conversation history, timestamps) is already in the `conversations` and `messages` tables.\n\n---\n\nIs this simple enough, or should we simplify further?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":77923,"output":158,"cacheRead":2752,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":80833,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773493055579}}
