{"type":"message","id":"e986db1c","parentId":"4aa9e2c3","timestamp":"2026-03-14T13:47:34.743Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good question! Let me clarify:\n\n---\n\n## Peer ID vs Contact Entry\n\n**Peer ID** is unique per person (e.g., `ou_abc123...`).\n\nBut one person can contact you through multiple channels:\n\n| peer_id | peer_name | channel |\n|---------|-----------|---------|\n| `ou_abc123` | Alice | feishu |\n| `ou_abc123` | Alice | telegram |\n\nSo the **composite primary key** is `(peer_id, channel)` — this allows:\n- Same person across multiple channels\n- Each channel entry is unique\n\n---\n\n## Alternative: Single Row with Channel List\n\nIf you prefer one row per person:\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE contacts (\n  peer_id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  peer_name TEXT,\n  channels TEXT  -- JSON: '[\"feishu\", \"telegram\"]'\n);\n```\n\n---\n\n## Which Do You Prefer?\n\n| Option | Pros | Cons |\n|--------|------|------|\n| **Composite PK** | Clean queries, easy to add channels | Multiple rows per person |\n| **JSON channels** | One row per person | JSON parsing needed |\n\nI prefer **composite PK** for cleaner queries. What do you think?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":84016,"output":247,"cacheRead":2752,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":87015,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773496010560}}
{"type":"message","id":"5c819e2a","parentId":"e986db1c","timestamp":"2026-03-14T13:50:55.555Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54623524b4a4c36c64cb0151d48\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-03-14 21:50 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b54623524b4a4c36c64cb0151d48]\n任亚伦: does compsite pk works? and we use contacts channles for?"}],"timestamp":1773496255542}}
{"type":"message","id":"6e7b9cf0","parentId":"5c819e2a","timestamp":"2026-03-14T13:51:23.273Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good questions! Let me clarify:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Does Composite PK Work?\n\n**Yes!** SQLite supports composite primary keys:\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE contacts (\n  peer_id TEXT,\n  peer_name TEXT,\n  channel TEXT,\n  PRIMARY KEY (peer_id, channel)\n);\n```\n\nThis means:\n- `('ou_abc123', 'Alice', 'feishu')` ✅\n- `('ou_abc123', 'Alice', 'telegram')` ✅\n- `('ou_abc123', 'Alice', 'feishu')` ❌ (duplicate — blocked)\n\n---\n\n## 2. What is `contacts.channels` Used For?\n\nI think you're asking: **why do we need the contacts table at all?**\n\n**Purpose of `contacts` table:**\n- Store **peer_name** (friendly name like \"Alice\")\n- Map `peer_id` → `peer_name` for display\n\n**Without contacts table:**\n- We only have `peer_id` in conversations\n- No way to show \"Alice\" instead of `ou_abc123...`\n\n---\n\n## Simplified Design\n\nActually, maybe we don't need `channel` in contacts at all:\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE contacts (\n  peer_id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  peer_name TEXT\n);\n```\n\n**Channel is already in `conversations` table:**\n\n```sql\n-- conversations table\nconversation_id, peer_id, channel, chat_type, ...\n```\n\n---\n\n## Revised Schema\n\n| Table | Columns |\n|-------|---------|\n| **contacts** | `peer_id` (PK), `peer_name` |\n| **conversations** | `...`, `peer_id`, `channel`, `chat_type` |\n\nThis is simpler! Channel is per-conversation, not per-contact.\n\nWhat do you think?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":84498,"output":376,"cacheRead":2752,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":87626,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773496255550}}
