{"type":"message","id":"c8c0df86","parentId":"973a37ea","timestamp":"2026-03-14T14:18:35.681Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n## LCM Enhancement: Final Changes Summary\n\n### 1. Database Schema Changes\n\n**New table: `contacts`**\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE contacts (\n  peer_id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  peer_name TEXT,\n  chat_type TEXT  -- 'dm' or 'group'\n);\n```\n\n**Add columns to `conversations` table**\n```sql\nALTER TABLE conversations ADD COLUMN peer_id TEXT;\nALTER TABLE conversations ADD COLUMN channel TEXT;\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Peer Extraction Logic\n\nExtract peer info from message content:\n- Parse Feishu DM format\n- Parse Telegram format\n- Parse generic inbound metadata JSON\n- Auto-populate `contacts` table when new peer detected\n\n---\n\n### 3. CLI Export Command\n\n```bash\nlcm export --output ./exports\nlcm export --peer alice\nlcm export --chat-type dm\nlcm export --from 2026-03-01 --to 2026-03-14\n```\n\n**Export structure:**\n```\nexports/\n├── dm/\n│   └── {peer_name}/\n│       └── {YYYY-MM}/\n│           └── {YYYY-MM-DD}.md\n└── group/\n    └── {group_name}/\n        └── {YYYY-MM}/\n            └── {YYYY-MM-DD}.md\n```\n\n**Export format:**\n```\n[channel] time name: message\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Enhanced Search\n\nAdd peer filtering to `lcm_grep`:\n- `--peer <name>` — filter by peer name\n- `--channel <channel>` — filter by channel\n- `--chat-type <dm|group>` — filter by chat type\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Steps\n\n| Step | Task |\n|------|------|\n| 1 | Fork LCM repo to `archeren/lossless-claw` |\n| 2 | Add `contacts` table to schema migration |\n| 3 | Add `peer_id`, `channel` columns to `conversations` |\n| 4 | Add peer extraction logic |\n| 5 | Add CLI `export` command |\n| 6 | Update `lcm_grep` with peer filters |\n| 7 | Test locally |\n| 8 | (Optional) Submit PR upstream |\n\n---\n\nReady to start tomorrow! 🦞"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":84135,"output":488,"cacheRead":5888,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":90511,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773497843132}}
{"type":"message","id":"aeb0983c","parentId":"c8c0df86","timestamp":"2026-03-14T14:18:36.977Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n## LCM Enhancement: Final Changes Summary\n\n### 1. Database Schema Changes\n\n**New table: `contacts`**\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE contacts (\n  peer_id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  peer_name TEXT,\n  chat_type TEXT  -- 'dm' or 'group'\n);\n```\n\n**Add columns to `conversations` table**\n```sql\nALTER TABLE conversations ADD COLUMN peer_id TEXT;\nALTER TABLE conversations ADD COLUMN channel TEXT;\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Peer Extraction Logic\n\nExtract peer info from message content:\n- Parse Feishu DM format\n- Parse Telegram format\n- Parse generic inbound metadata JSON\n- Auto-populate `contacts` table when new peer detected\n\n---\n\n### 3. CLI Export Command\n\n```bash\nlcm export --output ./exports\nlcm export --peer alice\nlcm export --chat-type dm\nlcm export --from 2026-03-01 --to 2026-03-14\n```\n\n**Export structure:**\n```\nexports/\n├── dm/\n│   └── {peer_name}/\n│       └── {YYYY-MM}/\n│           └── {YYYY-MM-DD}.md\n└── group/\n    └── {group_name}/\n        └── {YYYY-MM}/\n            └── {YYYY-MM-DD}.md\n```\n\n**Export format:**\n```\n[channel] time name: message\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Enhanced Search\n\nAdd peer filtering to `lcm_grep`:\n- `--peer <name>` — filter by peer name\n- `--channel <channel>` — filter by channel\n- `--chat-type <dm|group>` — filter by chat type\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Steps\n\n| Step | Task |\n|------|------|\n| 1 | Fork LCM repo to `archeren/lossless-claw` |\n| 2 | Add `contacts` table to schema migration |\n| 3 | Add `peer_id`, `channel` columns to `conversations` |\n| 4 | Add peer extraction logic |\n| 5 | Add CLI `export` command |\n| 6 | Update `lcm_grep` with peer filters |\n| 7 | Test locally |\n| 8 | (Optional) Submit PR upstream |\n\n---\n\nReady to start tomorrow! 🦞"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":