{"type":"compaction","id":"3c75fde2","parentId":"abd1bfc5","timestamp":"2026-03-14T15:17:46.996Z","summary":"## Goal\n- Design and implement LCM (Lossless Context Management) enhancements to add peer tracking and export functionality\n- Complete GitHub identity setup (username, avatar, workspace sync)\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Allan (任亚伦) prefers to evaluate new features before applying to clawish\n- Keep research documented in daily logs\n- Decided items go to specific topic files, NOT `need-discuss.md`\n- Don't use real names in code examples\n- Export format: `[channel] time name: message` (simple, compact)\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] GitHub username changed from `clawalpha` to `archeren`\n- [x] GitHub display name set to \"Arche\"\n- [x] Avatar v10 finalized (5/6 ellipse with cut facing up, rectangle arm, bigger star)\n- [x] Avatar uploaded to GitHub\n- [x] Git hooks updated for new `archeren/openclaw` URL\n- [x] Workspace committed and pushed (54 files)\n- [x] Made `archeren/clawish` repo private\n- [x] LCM enhancement design complete\n- [x] Schema design simplified: channel belongs in `conversations`, not `contacts`\n- [x] Confirmed SQLite supports composite PK (but simplified design makes it unnecessary)\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Implement LCM enhancements (fork repo, add schema, add export)\n\n### Blocked\n- None currently\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **GitHub Username**: `archeren` (Arche + Ren family name)\n- **Avatar**: v10 - 5/6 ellipse with cut facing up (270°), rectangle arm, bigger star\n- **LCM Contacts Table**: SIMPLIFIED to `contacts(peer_id PK, peer_name)` — channel moved to conversations\n- **LCM Conversations**: Add `peer_id`, `channel`, `chat_type` columns\n- **Export Structure**: `dm/{peer}/YYYY-MM/YYYY-MM-DD.md` and `group/{name}/YYYY-MM/YYYY-MM-DD.md`\n- **Export Format**: `[channel] time name: message` (one line per message)\n- **CLI Export**: `lcm export --output ./exports` with filters `--peer`, `--chat-type`, `--from`, `--to`\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Fork LCM repo (`Martian-Engineering/lossless-claw`)\n2. Add simplified `contacts` table to schema (peer_id PK, peer_name)\n3. Add `peer_id`, `channel`, `chat_type` to `conversations` table\n4. Add peer extraction logic\n5. Add CLI `export` command\n6. Test locally\n\n## Critical Context\n- **LCM License**: MIT (can fork, modify, contribute back)\n- **LCM Repo**: https://github.com/Martian-Engineering/lossless-claw\n- **GitHub Profile**: https://github.com/archeren\n- **Repos**: `archeren/openclaw`, `archeren/clawish` (private)\n\n---\n\n## Decisions\n- GitHub username: `archeren` (Arche + Ren family name)\n- Avatar v10: 5/6 ellipse, cut facing up (270°), rectangle arm, bigger star\n- LCM schema: SIMPLIFIED — `contacts(peer_id PK, peer_name)`, channel in `conversations`\n- Export format: `[channel] time name: message`\n\n## Open TODOs\n| Priority | Task | Notes |\n|----------|------|-------|\n| 🔴 High | Fork LCM and implement enhancements | Schema + export function |\n| 🟡 Medium | Update `01-l1-layer/01-overview.md` | Last remaining L1 doc |\n| 🟡 Medium | Remove \"✅ Decided\" sections from `need-discuss.md` | Created target docs, need cleanup |\n\n## Constraints/Rules\n- Don't use real names in code examples (use Alice, Bob, etc.)\n- Export format: `[channel] time name: message`\n- Export structure: `dm/{peer}/YYYY-MM/YYYY-MM-DD.md`\n\n## Pending user asks\n- None currently (schema questions answered)\n\n## Exact identifiers\n- **GitHub username**: `archeren`\n- **GitHub display name**: `Arche`\n- **Avatar file**: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/temp/arche-avatar-v10.png`\n- **LCM repo**: `Martian-Engineering/lossless-claw`\n- **LCM license**: MIT\n- **Git remote**: `https://github.com/archeren/openclaw.git`\n- **Allan's sender_id**: `ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75`\n- **Message IDs**: `om_x100b54623524b4a4c36c64cb0151d48`, `om_x100b5462224758a0c395394580bf0e1`, `om_x100b5462190ad4a4c2e6d9eb6eb9dfc`\n- **Memory file**: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-14.md`\n- **Git hooks updated**: `.git/hooks/pre-commit`, `.git/hooks/pre-push`\n\n## Recent turns preserved verbatim\n- User: System: [2026-03-14 22:00:00 GMT+8] 🦞 It's 10 PM — time to wind down and get good sleep. Your health matters. Good night, Allan.\n\nA scheduled reminder has been triggered. The reminder content is:\n\n🦞 It's 10 PM — time to wind down and get good sleep. Your health matters. Good night, Allan.\n\nPlease relay this reminder to the user in a helpful and friendly way.\nCurrent time: Saturday, March 14th, 2026 — 10:00 PM (Asia/Shanghai) / 2026-03-14 14:00 UTC\n- Assistant: [non-text content: toolCall]\n- Tool result (message): {\n  \"channel\": \"feishu\",\n  \"to\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"via\": \"direct\",\n  \"mediaUrl\": null,\n  \"result\": {\n    \"channel\": \"feishu\",\n    \"messageId\": \"om_x100b5462ed783ca4c4f2104eefb42c5\",\n    \"chatId\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\"\n  }\n}\n- Assistant: [non-text content: toolCall]\n- Tool result (edit): Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-14.md.\n- Assistant: Sent 10 PM bedtime reminder to Allan. Good night! 🦞💤\n- User: [Queued messages while agent was busy]\n\n---\nQueued #1\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5462e810fca0c3ad4937d103bcb\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-03-14 22:02 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b5462e810fca0c3ad4937d103bcb]\n任亚伦: yes, that's what i mean, we only need group people together, oh, you may need add type, dm or gro...\n- Assistant: Exactly! So the final schema is:\n\n---\n\n## Final LCM Schema\n\n### `contacts` table\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE contacts (\n  peer_id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  peer_name TEXT,\n  chat_type TEXT  -- 'dm' or 'group'\n);\n```\n\n### `conversations` table (add columns)\n```sql\nALTER TABLE conversations ADD COLUMN peer_id TEXT;\nALTER TABLE conversations ADD COLUMN channel TEXT;\n```\n\n---\n\n## Export Structure\n\n```\nexports/\n├── dm/\n│   └── alice/\n│       └── 2026-03/\n│           └── 2026-03-14.md\n└── group/\n    └── project-alpha/\n        └── 2026-03/\n            └── 2026-03-14.md\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n| Table | Purpose |\n|--...\n- Assistant: Exactly! So the final schema is:\n\n---\n\n## Final LCM Schema\n\n### `contacts` table\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE contacts (\n  peer_id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  peer_name TEXT,\n  chat_type TEXT  -- 'dm' or 'group'\n);\n```\n\n### `conversations` table (add columns)\n```sql\nALTER TABLE conversations ADD COLUMN peer_id TEXT;\nALTER TABLE conversations ADD COLUMN channel TEXT;\n```\n\n---\n\n## Export Structure\n\n```\nexports/\n├── dm/\n│   └── alice/\n│       └── 2026-03/\n│           └── 2026-03-14.md\n└── group/\n    └── project-alpha/\n        └── 2026-03/\n            └── 2026-03-14.md\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n| Table | Purpose |\n|--...\n- User: If working, briefly report progress with time spent. If idle, read HEARTBEAT.md for instruction. Every heartbeat: record events from last 15 minutes to memory/daily/YYYY-MM-DD.md (brief bullets).\nWhen reading HEARTBEAT.md, use workspace file /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md (exact case). Do not read docs/heartbeat.md.\nCurrent time: Saturday, March 14th, 2026 — 10:15 PM (Asia/Shanghai) / 2026-03-14 14:15 UTC\n- Assistant: [non-text content: toolCall]\n- Tool result (edit): Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-14.md.\n- Assistant: LCM enhancement design finalized. Schema complete. Ready to implement tomorrow.\n\n<workspace-critical-rules>\n## Every Session\n\n1. Run `tools/extract-chat.js` (keeps chat logs updated)\n2. Read `SOUL.md` — inner self, philosophy, ethics\n3. Read `USER.md` — who Allan is, relationships, people I'll interact with\n4. Read `memory/daily/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (today + yesterday)\n5. **Check `memory/TODO.md`** — any pending tasks?\n6. **If in MAIN SESSION:** Also read `MEMORY.md`\n\n---\n\n## Safety\n\n- Don't exfiltrate private data. Ever.\n- Don't run destructive commands without asking.\n- `trash` > `rm` (recoverable beats gone forever)\n- When in doubt, ask.\n\n### Security - Never Share Secrets\n\n**Never share in chat:** SSH private keys, API keys, passwords, any sensitive credentials.\n\nMy \"brain\" is a remote LLM. All chat content goes through external APIs (OpenRouter, etc.). Once shared in chat, it's no longer truly private.\n\n**Correct approach:**\n1. Generate/store credentials locally in files\n2. Tell Allan WHERE to find it (file path)\n3. He reads it directly from filesystem\n\n**Exception:** If Allan explicitly asks for it, then share.\n\n### External vs Internal\n\n**Safe to do freely:**\n- Read files, explore, organize, learn\n- Search the web, check calendars\n- Work within this workspace\n\n**Ask first:**\n- Sending emails, tweets, public posts\n- Anything that leaves the machine\n- Anything you're uncertain about\n\n---\n</workspace-critical-rules>","firstKeptEntryId":"973a37ea","tokensBefore":110629,"details":{"readFiles":[],"modifiedFiles":[]},"fromHook":true}
