{"type":"message","id":"34b9b98f","parentId":"3972636e","timestamp":"2026-03-14T16:44:23.368Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is asking what the lcm_update_peer tool is for. Let me explain its purpose clearly.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"The `lcm_update_peer` tool is for **populating the contacts table** with real peer information.\n\n---\n\n## The Problem\n\nWe added a `contacts` table and `peer_id`/`channel` columns to conversations, but they start empty. Without data:\n- `lcm_export` exports to `/unknown/` folders\n- `lcm_grep --peerId` finds nothing\n\n---\n\n## The Solution\n\n`lcm_update_peer` populates the contacts:\n\n```bash\nlcm_update_peer --peerId 'user:ou_abc123' --peerName 'Alice' --channel feishu --chatType dm\n```\n\nThis:\n1. Creates/updates the contact record\n2. Links the current conversation to that contact\n\n---\n\n## How It Gets Called\n\n**Option 1: Manual** — You call it when you want to tag a conversation\n\n**Option 2: Automatic** — OpenClaw can call it when receiving inbound messages\n\nFor example, when a Feishu message comes in with:\n```json\n{\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_abc123\",\n  \"sender\": \"Alice\",\n  \"channel\": \"feishu\",\n  \"chat_type\": \"dm\"\n}\n```\n\nOpenClaw would call `lcm_update_peer` automatically with that info.\n\n---\n\n## Do We Need Automatic Integration?\n\nRight now it's manual. To make it automatic, we'd need to modify OpenClaw core to:\n1. Extract peer info from inbound metadata\n2. Call `lcm_update_peer` on message receipt\n\nWant me to add that integration to OpenClaw? Or leave it manual for now?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":93939,"output":372,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":94311,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773506626240}}
{"type":"message","id":"12b301c0","parentId":"34b9b98f","timestamp":"2026-03-14T16:45:17.749Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b546d47000ca0c1041117b456307\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-15 00:45 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b546d47000ca0c1041117b456307]\n任亚伦: yes, you should. otherwise, will it break?"}],"timestamp":1773506717732}}
{"type":"message","id":"d528415d","parentId":"12b301c0","timestamp":"2026-03-14T16:46:07.888Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking if the LCM enhancement will break if we don't add automatic peer extraction to OpenClaw core. Let me think about this:\n\n1. The `contacts` table and `peer_id`/`channel` columns are optional - they're just foreign keys that can be NULL\n2. Without automatic population, the export would just go to `/unknown/` folders\n3. The grep filters would still work, just return fewer results\n4. Nothing would \"break\" - it just wouldn't be as useful\n\nBut the user wants automatic integration. Let me check how OpenClaw processes inbound messages and where I can add the call to `lcm_update_peer`.\n\nI need to find where OpenClaw receives inbound messages and extracts metadata. This would likely be in the channel plugins (feishu, telegram, etc.) or in the core message processing.\n\nLet me look at the OpenClaw codebase to understand where to add this integration.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"No, it won't break — everything still works, just without peer organization:\n- Export goes to `/unknown/` folders\n- Search filters work but return less useful results\n\nBut you're right — automatic integration makes it actually useful. Let me add it to OpenClaw."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_15b4abb2be864b04a59e03d7","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /home/ubuntu/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw -name \"*.ts\" -type f | xargs grep -l \"inbound\\|sender_id\\|chat_id\" 2>/dev/null | head -10"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":94510,"output":401,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":94911,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773506717742}}
