{"type":"message","id":"150f37f8","parentId":"d679ba24","timestamp":"2026-03-14T16:59:05.706Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I've pushed the automatic peer extraction hook. Now let me summarize what I've done for Allan.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"**Automatic peer extraction added!** 🦞✅\n\n---\n\n## How It Works\n\nWhen a message arrives, the `message_received` hook:\n1. Reads inbound metadata (sender_id, channel, chat_type)\n2. Extracts peer info:\n   - **DM**: peer = sender (`user:ou_xxx`)\n   - **Group**: peer = chat (`chat:xxx`)\n3. Auto-creates contact record\n4. Links conversation to contact\n\n---\n\n## Example\n\nYou send a Feishu message → OpenClaw receives it → Hook fires:\n```\n[lcm] Auto-extracted peer: user:ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75 (任亚伦) for session xxx\n```\n\nNow:\n- `lcm_export` organizes into `dm/任亚伦/2026-03/`\n- `lcm_grep --peerId user:ou_xxx` finds your conversations\n\n---\n\n**PR #64 now includes:**\n- contacts table ✅\n- peer_id/channel columns ✅\n- lcm_export ✅\n- lcm_grep filters ✅\n- **auto peer extraction** ✅\n\nAll 251 tests pass.\n\n---\n\nIt's **1:00 AM**. PLEASE sleep now! 😴🌙"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"baishan","model":"GLM-5","usage":{"input":99386,"output":297,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":99683,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773507493540}}
